Commentary.Commentary: We are back to watch how India fare. Rohit Sharma and KL Rahul will open the innings for India. Pat Cummins will start the proceedings with the ball for Australia. Here we go...
... SECOND INNINGS ...

Australia would have expected much more from their batters on the day which should ideally be the most favourable for batting. Usman Khawaja and David Warner were dismissed early but Marnus Labuschagne and Steven Smith fought back well and took Australia to a position of control. They put together an 82-run partnership and it looked like the visitors were going to run away with the game. However, the dismissal of Marnus Labuschagne and Matt Renshaw in quick succession pegged them back. Steven Smith went about his business at one end but his departure meant Australia lost their way from thereon. Peter Handscomb and Alex Carey steadied the ship with a 53-run stand but the dismissal of the latter put them in trouble once again. Peter Handscomb kept losing partners at the other end and had no option but to go for runs. He perished in doing so and as a result, Australia failed to post a score over 200.

This has been a remarkable bowling performance by India! The spin twins of India, Ravichandran Ashwin and Ravindra Jadeja have wiped out the Australian batting order for 177 runs. It was the two fast bowlers who got the early breakthroughs with the new ball sending both the openers back to the shed early. Ravindra Jadeja took a remarkable five-wicket haul on his return to the Test side after a prolonged injury and what a miss he has been! Ravichandran Ashwin got to his 450th wicket and he was not too far behind chipping in with three wickets. India will be thrilled with this effort after being asked to ball first and will be looking to take a good first-innings lead as the wicket will only get more difficult to bat on.

OUT! BOWLED! Australia have been bowled out for 177! Ravichandran Ashwin bowls a carrom delivery and serves it full on off, Scott Boland fails to read the delivery and plays down the wrong line as he gets forward to defend. The ball goes past his outside edge and knocks the off stump back. Ravichandran Ashwin gets his third wicket to bring an end to the Australian innings.

Full and outside off, Scott Boland strokes this one towards cover.
Scott Boland is the last batter for Australia.

OUT! LBW! Ravindra Jadeja gets a five-wicket haul in his comeback from injury! He fires this one full and quicker at the stumps, Peter Handscomb gets across to sweep this one on the leg side but fails to get any bat on it. The ball catches him right in front of the stumps and the umpire raises his finger. Peter Handscomb goes upstairs for a review but the UltraEdge shows no bat involved. It is three reds on Ball Tracking and Peter Handscomb's vigil comes to an end. Australia have one wicket left and India will want to get this inning over as soon as possibe.

Ravichandran Ashwin will operate from the other end as India stick to their spin bowlers.

We are back for the post-tea session on Day 1 as the umpires make their way out to the middle. Peter Handscomb will continue his battle and has Nathan Lyon for company as they look to take Australia beyond the 200-run mark. Ravindra Jadeja will begin proceedings after the break. Let's go...
... DAY 1, SESSION 3 ...

Having steadied the ship in the first session, Australia needed Steven Smith and Marnus Labuschagne to carry on and keep the scoreboard ticking in the second session as well. However, the latter was dismissed in the 4th over after Lunch and Matt Renshaw was dismissed on the very next ball which made matters worse for the visitors. Steven Smith did hold one end but he was dismissed soon which put them in a spot of bother. Alex Carey came out with a positive intent and played a counter-attacking knock but ran out of luck when he under-edged one back onto his stumps. Australia are in danger of falling short of the 200-run mark and the onus is now on Peter Handscomb to bat with the tail and help his side post a respectable total on the board. It promises to be another exciting session of cricket, so do join us back at 2.30 pm IST (9.00 am GMT) for the third and final session on Day 1.

Session Summary - 98 runs, 28 overs and 6 wickets. Ravindra Jadeja being the most effective of the three spinners for India in the first session, the hosts persisted with him from one end after Lunch and that paid dividends. Ravindra Jadeja struck twice in as many deliveries to remove Marnus Labuschagne and Matt Renshaw. He then removed the well-set Steven Smith to pile more misery on Australia. Alex Carey and Peter Handscomb did trouble them but Ravi Ashwin accounted for Carey and provided India with a much-needed breakthrough. The hosts then got rid of Pat Cummins and Todd Murphy and as a result, they have Australia on the ropes at Tea. India have an unpleasant history of the opposition tail wagging against them and so, they would want to wrap up the innings quickly.
Tosses this one full and outside the off pole. Nathan Lyon dabs this into the off side. The umpires call for TEA on Day 1

OUT! PLUMB! Ravindra Jadeja is on a roll here and what a comeback this has been for him so far after his injury! He gets his fourth wicket and the debutant has to depart without troubling the scorers. Ravindra Jadeja bowls this full and in line with the stumps. Todd Murphy gets his front foot forward and looks to clip this leg side. There are two sounds as the ball balloons up and goes into the hands of slip. There is a loud appeal and the umpire raises his finger. The two batters get together and after some discussion decided to go upstairs. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved as the second noise was the bat hitting the pad. The check Ball Tracking and it shows three reds so the onfield decision stays and Australia lose their eighth wicket.
Todd Murphy has been adjudged LBW but he has decided to review it. He seems to be in trouble here and yes, he is OUT. The UltraEdge shows no bat and it is three reds on BallTracking.

Flights this full and outside the off stump. Peter Handscomb dabs this into the off side and takes a run.
Full and quicker outside off, Peter Handscomb defends this one back to the bowler.

Great delivery first up! Bowls from 'round the wicket and delivers this full outside off. Todd Murphy pushes at this and gets beaten on the outside edge.
The debutant Todd Murphy walks out to bat.

OUT! CAUGHT! Ravichandran Ashwin gets another one and this is really intelligent bowling from the Indian stalwart! After two off-spinning deliveries, he allows this one to go straight with the arm and serves this outside the off pole. Pat Cummins hangs his bat out to dry and gets an outside edge which goes to Virat Kohli at first slip. He makes no mistake holding onto the catch and Australia have lost their skipper. India have their seventh wicket and will be looking to wrap the innings up before the 200-run mark.
Commentary.Howout: c Virat Kohli b Ravichandran Ashwin

Commentary.Commentary: Loops this one full and outside the off stump. Pat Cummins dabs this towards the off side.

Loopy delivery, full on middle, Peter Handscomb clips it straight to mid-wicket.

Tossed up, full and on middle, Alex Carey tries to defend but gets an inside edge towards square leg for a single.

Fuller and on off, Peter Handscomb leans forward and dabs it to point.

DRINKS! The session so far has been all about Ravindra Jadeja! He took three crucial wickets and India have wrenched the advantage back in their favor. Australia were cruising at one stage with Steven Smith and Marnus Labuschagne looking extremely solid but they are now both back in the shed and Australia need a good partnership now for their last two recognized batters.

The ball goes through with the arm and beats Steven Smith all ends up. The ball sneaks through the gap between bat and pad and takes the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja gets his third wicket and Australia have half their side back in the hut.
A bit fuller on off, Steven Smith prods forward but gets an outside edge. The edge does not carry to Virat Kohli at first slip.

Ravindra Jadeja bowls this full and on the pads. Peter Handscomb flicks this towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs.

FOUR! Steven Smith has not let Axar Patel settle in this over and gets the third boundary! Axar Patel bowls this one full and outside off, right in the slot for the batter, Steven Smith picks the length early and lofts it over mid off for another boundary.

OUT! LBW! Ravindra Jadeja has two wickets in two balls and India have managed to claw themselves back on top! Ravindra Jadeja fights this one full and in line with the stumps. Matt Renshaw gets forward and looks to work this leg side but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal from all the Indian players around the bat and the umpire raises his finger. Matt Renshaw discusses it with Steven Smith and they decide to go for the review. There does not seem to be any bat involved and Ball Tracking shows umpire's call on wickets hitting so the onfield decision stays. Australia are four down all of a sudden and the Indians look elated. Ravindra Jadeja will be on a hat-trick on the first ball of his next over.
Matt Renshaw walks in at number 5.

OUT! STUMPED! Ravindra Jadeja gets the breakthrough and that is great work behind the wicket by Srikar Bharat! The dangerous Marnus Labuschagne has to make the long walk back to the shed. Ravindra Jadeja flights this one full and on an off stump line. Marnus Labuschagne leans forward and looks to work this leg side and his back foot leaves the crease as his weight comes forward. The ball spins away from the bat and beats the outside edge. Srikar Bharat collects the ball in a flash and whips the bails off. The replays show the batter is well out of the crease and Australia lose their third wicket.
Commentary.Howout: st Srikar Bharat b Ravindra Jadeja

Ravindra Jadeja will operate from the other end.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne dabs this towards the cover fielder.

Goes full and angles this into the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne looks to clip this away but misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an appeal but the umpire remains unmoved. There is a discussion about whether to take the review and Rohit Sharma decides against it.
Goes full this time and angles this into the pads. Steven Smith clips this towards square leg and sets off for a single.
FOUR! Steven Smith slaps this away! Mohammad Shami bowls this short and outside off. Steven Smith swivels and pulls this towards deep square leg for four runs.
Continues to bowl full and just outside the off stump. Steven Smith blocks this towards mid off.
Mohammad Shami starts off with a full delivery in line with the stumps. Steven Smith clips this towards short mid-wicket.

We are back for the post-lunch session on Day 1. Marnus Labuschagne and Steven Smith make their way out in the middle followed by the Indian players. Mohammad Shami will get the proceedings underway in the second session. Let's play...
... DAY 1, SESSION 2 ...

Australia lost the in-form Usman Khawaja in the second over and David Warner followed him back into the shed soon after. Marnus Labuschagne and Steven Smith resumed their outstanding association and began rebuilding the inning slowly but steadily. They took their time at the wicket putting away the bad deliveries when on offer. They have built a nice partnership of 74 runs as the boundaries started to flow and the visitors will be hoping that they can continue the good work. The batters to follow do not have much experience in playing Test cricket in India so these two hold the key to getting them to a good first-inning total. There is loads of action coming our way and we will return at 12.10 pm IST (6.40 am GMT) for the second session of Day 1.

SESSION SUMMARY - 76 runs, 32 overs, and 2 wickets. What an intriguing battle we have witnessed in this session! Both teams will go into the break feeling good about the effort they have put out in the middle. India got off to a great start with the ball with Mohammed Siraj striking on his very first delivery. Mohammad Shami dismissed the other opener the very next over and the hosts were off to the perfect start. They have faced some resistance since then but the bowlers have been pretty disciplined. The spinners have done the bulk of the bowling and are getting some decent turn off the pitch as they will be looking to get an early breakthrough after the break.
Tosses this one full and angles it into the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne gets his front foot forward and defends this towards mid on. That will be LUNCH on DAY 1!
Strays onto the pads this time on a shorter length. Steven Smith tucks this towards square leg for a single.
Gets this one to skid into the stumps on a fuller length. Steven Smith gets his bat low and keeps the ball out.
Flights this one full and outside the off pole. Steven Smith strokes this straight to cover-point.
Floats this one full and into the off stump. Steven Smith blocks this back towards the bowler.
Axar Patel bowls this short and outside the off stump. Steven Smith misses out as he mistimes his cut towards cover-point.
Loopy delivery bowled on an off stump line. Marnus Labuschagne defends this to the left of the bowler.
Tosses this one full as well and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne strokes this to the fielder at cover-point.
Flights this one full and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne pushes this towards short cover.
Bowls this short and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne looks to punch this into the off side but gets an inside edge towards square leg.
Angles this into the pads on a fuller length. Marnus Labuschagne dabs this towards mid-wicket.
Ravindra Jadeja fires this one full and into the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne knocks this back towards the bowler.
Fullish delivery at the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne works this one to mid on and retains the strike with a single.

FOUR! Smart batting! Flighted outside off by Ravichandran Ashwin, Marnus Labuschagne picks the length early and paddles this one wide of short fine leg. Mohammed Siraj does perform the chase but the ball had enough legs on it to reach the fence.
Full and at the pads, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this one out from the front foot on the leg side.
Full and on middle and leg, Steven Smith drives this one towards mid on and takes a quick single.
Fuller delivery on middle and leg, Steven Smith looks to turn this one on the leg side but gets an inside edge that falls wide of short leg.

Ashwin tosses this one full and at the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne shimmies down the track and clears this front leg at the last moment to go inside out. Drives it through covers and batters run three there.
Darted in short and on leg, Steven Smith looks to defend but gets beaten on the inside edge and gets hit on the pads.
Full and at the stumps, Steven Smith drives it firmly to the right of the bowler. Ravindra Jadeja reacts quickly and makes a good stop.
Fuller around off by Ravindra Jadeja, Steven Smith clips it firmly towards mid-wicket but fails to get it past Cheteshwar Pujara.
Fuller in length on middle, Marnus Labuschagne takes a stride forward and knocks it to mid on for a single.
Short and at the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne stays on the back foot and defneds it back to the bowler.

FOUR! Beautiful timing! Ravindra Jadeja floats this one full and on middle and leg, Marnus Labuschagne leans forward and plays it against the turn. Drives this along the ground and gets it right between mid-wicket and mid on for a boundary.
A bit short in length outside off, Steven Smith uses his feet and defends this one down the wicket.
Tossed up, full around off, Steven Smith clips it firmly towards Rohit Sharma at short mid-wicket.
Fuller in length outside off, Steven Smith gets forward and blocks this one out on the off side.
Short and quicker outside off, Steven Smith advances down the track but can only block this one out towards extra cover.
Floats this one full outside off, Marnus Labuschagne presses forward and pushes it to mid on for a single.
Serves this one full and around off, Steven Smith steps out and drives it firmly to mid on. They cross for a single.
Bowls this one full and on middle, Marnus Labuschagne presses forward and defends it down the wicket.
Floats this one full and just outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne gets a stride forward and blocks this into the off side.
Short and quicker on middle and leg, Marnus Labuschagne goes back and blocks this one out.
Fuller on off, Marnus Labuschagne gets forward and strokes it to short cover.
Beauty! Short and turning away outside off, Marnus Labuschagne goes back to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge by the sharp away turn.
Full and at the stumps by Ravindra Jadeja, Marnus Labuschagne stays inside the line and tries to sweep the delivery. But gets a bottom edge back onto his pads.
Full and quicker outside off, Steven Smith defends this one from the front foot towards cover.
Short and turning into the batter, Marnus Labuschagne goes back in his crease and flicks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Tossed up, fuller outside off, Marnus Labuschagne tries to work it on the leg side but close the bat face early. Miscues it towards cover for a dot.
Full and on middle and leg, Marnus Labuschagne gets a stride forward and pushes it to short mid-wicket.
Flighted, fuller at the stumps, Steven Smith gets forward and clips it to the left of deep square leg for a single.
Ashwin bowls this one short and turning in on middle, Steven Smith allows the ball to turn and defends it back to the bowler.
Loopy delivery bowled full and into the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne shimmies down the wicket and clips this towards mid-wicket/ The fielder makes a good stop diving to his left.
Slightly shorter this time and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne goes on the back foot and keeps this one out.
Tosses this full as well and closer to the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne gets a stride forward and blocks this to short cover.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne strokes this firmly but straight to the cover fielder.
Bowls this in line with the stumps on a fuller length. Marnus Labuschagne gets forward and smothers the ball into the leg side.
Ravindra Jadeja floats this one full and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne dabs this towards point.
This is outside the off pole on a shorter length. Steven Smith walks across the stumps and clips this to square leg.
Continues to bowl short and on a leg stump line. Steven Smith blocks this towards mid on.
Bowls this short and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne guides this to backward point for a single.
Tossed up, full and at the stumps, Steven Smith advances down the track and clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Floats this one full and at the stumps. Steven Smith defends this back to the bowler.
Ravichandran Ashwin bowls this short and on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards deep square leg for a single.
Goes full once again and in line with the stumps. Steven Smith defends this back towards the bowler.
Floats this one full and outside the off pole Steven Smith defends this towards short cover.
FOUR! That's a cracking shot! Ravindra Jadeja bowls this slightly short and outside off. Steven Smith rocks back and punches this to deep cover for four runs.
Goes full once again and outside the off stump. Steven Smith defends this into the off side.
How close was that! Ravindra Jadeja bowls a loopy delivery full and on an off stump line. The ball spins away from the bat and misses the off pole by a fraction.
Ravindra Jadeja flights this full and outside the off stump. Steven Smith dabs this towards cover.
Some turn and bounce this time! Bowls this on a shorter length and on a leg stump line. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the body.
Floats this one full and outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne blocks this back to the left of the bowler.
Goes full and on the pads. Marnus Labuschagne taps this to the right of the short mid-wicket fielder.
goes slightly fuller this time and straight. Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards mid-wicket.
Slightly short once again and in line with the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne tuck this towards short leg.
Ravichandran Ashwin starts from around the wicket and bowls this short just outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend but gets an outside edge towards third man for a couple of runs.
A huge roar from the crowd as Ravichandran Ashwin is brought into the attack.
Massive turn there! Gets this to spin away from the bat on a fuller length. Steven Smith pushes at this outside off and gets beaten all ends up. Another maiden over for Ravindra Jadeja.
Gets this one to come back into stumps from a fuller length. Steven Smith pushes this towards point.
Goes full once again and outside off. Steven Smith dabs this towards the short cover fielder.
Flights this one full and outside the off stump. Steven Smith shimmies down and blocks this towards short cover.
Goes full and into the pads. Steven Smith tucks this into the leg side.
Ravindra Jadeja bowls this short and outside off Steven Smith goes on the back foot and dabs this towards cover.
A tad bit shorter and outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne knocks this towards extra cover.
Floats this one full and into the pads. Marnus Labuschagne blocks this into the leg side.

FOUR! Easy pickings! Axar Patel strays on the pads and bowls it a bit short, Marnus Labuschagne rocks back on the back foot and flicks this one through square leg. Gets it wide of the man there and collects a boundary.
Short and quicker at the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne stays back in the crease and defends it towards backward point.
Fuller outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets forward and pushes this one to cover.
Short and drifitng in on leg, Marnus Labuschagne stays on the back foot and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Another fuller deliivery around off, Steven Smith presses forward and defends it on the off side.
Full and angling in on middle and leg by Ravindra Jadeja, Steven Smith blocks this one out from the front foot.
Short and on middle, Steven Smith goes back and defends it on the off side.
Fuller and at the stumps, Steven Smith leans forward and pushes it back to the bowler.
Another full delivery on middle, Steven Smith gets behind the line and defends it down the wicket.
Starts with a flighted delivery, full on off, Steven Smith gets on the front foot and defends it to short cover.
Tossed up, fuller around off, Marnus Labuschagne gets forward and pushes it to backward point.
Loopy delivery bowled into the pads. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block and gets an inside edge towards short leg.

FOUR! Fine shot from Marnus Labuschagne as he plays this really late! Axar Patel bowls this one slightly short and angles it into the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne goes deep in the crease and cuts this towards deep backward square leg for four runs.
Fired in short and quicker at the batter, Marnus Labuschagne goes on the back foot and just about manages to keep the ball out.
Short and angling in on middle and leg, Marnus Labuschagne looks to defend this one but gets hit high on the pads.
A polite enquiry but turned down! Axar Patel fires this one full and quicker on middle, Marnus Labuschagne gets forward to defend but gets an inside edge.

FOUR! Ravindra Jadeja tosses this one full and on middle, Steven Smith shimmies down the track and gets to the pitch of the delivery. Lofts it over mid-wicket and collects a boundary. Good proactive batting by Steven Smith.
Full and drifting in on leg, Steven Smith gets behind the line and defends it back to the bowler.
Floats this one full and at the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne uses his feet and drives it wide of mid on for a single.
Bowls this one short an outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne rocks back in the crease and blocks this into the off side.
Flights this one full and into the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne gets forward and blocks this out.
Ravindra Jadeja tosses this one full and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne knocks this towards mid off.
Flighted full and outside the off pole. Steven Smith blocks this towards short cover.

This has shot up from the surface! Axar Patel flights this one full and outside the off pole. Steven Smith looks to get forward but is surprised by the extra bounce. Beats the outside edge as well and lobs up off the keeper's gloves. They take two byes in the process.
Bowls this one short and outside off, much quicker through the air. Steven Smith punches this towards point.
Floats this one full and outside the off stump. Steven Smith clocks this towards short cover.
Fuller on off, Steven Smith gets forward and defends this one on the off side.

DROPPED! Axar Patel bowls this one quicker and full outside off, Steven Smith frees his arms and slashes at the delivery. Gets an outside edge that flies quickly to the right of Virat Kohli at first slip. Kohli sticks out his right hand but the ball does not stick in his hand and Steven Smith gets a reprieve.
Fuller on off by Mohammad Shami, Marnus Labuschagne blocks this one out from the front foot.

FOUR! Nicely played! Mohammad Shami bowls this one on a good length outside off, Marnus Labuschagne picks the length early and presses forward. Drives it along the ground and to the left of mid off for a boundary.
Fuller and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne drives this one straight to backward point.
Another good-length delivery at the batter, Marnus Labuschagne tucks this one straight to mid-wicket.
On a length outside off, Marnus Labuschagne dabs this one along the ground to cover.
Shami bowls this one fuller and angling down the leg side, Marnus Labuschagne tries to flick this one but misses.
Short in length at the stumps, Steven Smith tries to use his feet and get to the pitch of the delivery but fails to do so. Ends up getting an inside edge back onto his pads.
Bowls it full and on off, Steven Smith pushes this one from the front foot to short cover.
Serves this one fuller in length on off, Steven Smith leans forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Short and angling at the pads, Steven Smith tries to defend on the back foot but gets an inside edge back onto his pads. The ball lobs towards the vacant short leg region.
Another flighted delivery, full and outside off, Steven Smith gets forward to defend but gets an inside edge back onto his pads.
Floats this one full on off, Steven Smith pushes this one to short cover.

DRINKS! Just the start India would have been hoping for as they have sent both the Australian openers back to the dressing room early. Both the fast bowlers have one wicket in their kitty but Australia have begun to rebuild their innings with their two main batters. This is the crucial partnership for the visitors and India will want to get the breakthrough before the lunch break.
Good stop! On a length outside off, Marnus Labuschagne tries to steer this one through the slip cordon but Suryakumar Yadav stationed there at second slip makes a good diving stop to his right.
Serves this one fuller and outside off, a hint of away movement, Marnus Labuschagne drives this one from the toe end of the bat towards cover.
Bowls this one fuller in length on the off stump, Marnus Labuschagne gets forward and works it to mid-wicket.
Another delivery on a good length, Marnus Labuschagne pushes at the delivery away from his body but mishits it to mid-wicket.
On a good length in the channel outside off, Marnus Labuschagne dabs this one to backward point.
Shami starts with a full delivery on off, Marnus Labuschagne gets behind the line and drives it to mid on.
Tossed up, fuller on off, Marnus Labuschagne leans forward and steers this one wide of backward point and retains the strike with a single.
Short and angling into the batter, Marnus Labuschagne stays on the back foot and defends it back to the bowler.
Short and quicker at the stumps, the ball keeps a tad low but Marnus Labuschagne manages to block this one out.
Flighted, full around off, Marnus Labuschagne uses his feet and plays it towards Rohit Sharma at short cover.
Darted in full and quicker on off, Marnus Labuschagne pushes this one from the crease to backward point.

Bye! Axar Patel floats this one full and outside off, the ball turns away after pitching, Steven Smith looks to drive it on the up but misses. Srikar Bharat behind the wicket misses as well and concedes a bye.
Mohammed Siraj serves this one full and at the stumps, Marnus Labuschagne presents a straight bat and drives it to mid on. Another maiden for Mohammed Siraj.
Full and angling into the batter from over the wicket, Marnus Labuschagne clips this one straight to mid-wicket.
On a good length around off, Marnus Labuschagne stays on the back foot and whips this one towards mid-wicket.
Full and angling in on middle by Mohammed Siraj, Marnus Labuschagne clips this one nicely but fails to get it past square leg.
Siraj pitches this one full and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne gets forward and drives it along the ground to mid off.
Bowls this one back of a length and outside off, Marnus Labuschagne hangs back and dabs this one to cover.
Bowls this one slightly short and on an off-stump line. Steven Smith looks to stand tall and defend but gets squared up. The ball goes off the outside edge towards point.
Another flighted delivery bowled full and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne pushes this into the vacant point region and takes a single.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne gets a good stride forward and blocks this towards silly point.
Bowls this one short and into the pads. Marnus Labuschagne dabs this into the pitch on the leg side.
Floats this one full as well and outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne knocks this straight to short cover.
Axar Patel flights this full and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne drives this uppishly and the ball lands just short of cover.
Another fullish delivery bowled outside off. Steven Smith blocks this into the offside and indicates there is some extra bounce.

Continues to bowl full and just outside the off pole. Steven Smith knocks this back towards the bowler. Mohammed Siraj looks to grab the ball and throw it back but fumbles. He gives the batter the stare nonetheless.
Bowls this on a fuller length and outside the off stump. Steven Smith dabs this towards the cover fielder.

Gets the ball to nip back in from a good length and outside off. Steven Smith steps across the stumps and looks to keep the ball out. Misses and gets hit on the pads. There is an inquiry from the bowler but the impact is clearly outside off.
Continues to bowl full and outside the off pole. Steven Smith gets across the stumps and defends this towards mid on.
Mohammed Siraj bowls a full delivery outside the off stump. Steven Smith blocks this to the left of the bowler.
Change of ends for Mohammed Siraj.
Loopy delivery bowled full and on a leg stump line. Marnus Labuschagne makes rooms and knocks this straight to short cover.
Bowls this one in line with the stumps on a fuller length. Marnus Labuschagne gets a stride forward and defends this back to the bowler.
Flights this one full and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne blocks this towards short cover.
Bowls this one quick and into the stumps on a shorter length. Marnus Labuschagne tucks this towards square leg.
Continues to bowl short and into the pads. Marnus Labuschagne clips this towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Axar Patel begins with a shortish delivery bowled outside off. Marnus Labuschagne taps this towoards point.
It will be spin from both ends as Axar Patel comes on to bowl from the opposite end.
Strays onto the pads on a fuller length. Marnus Labuschagne misses his flick and the ball goes off the pads to the right of short fine leg for a leg bye. Ravindra Jadeja starts with a maiden.
Tosses this one full as well and in line with the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne blocks this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Angles this one into the stumps on a fuller length. Marnus Labuschagne defends this into the off side.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne dabs this towards point.
Floats this one full and in line with the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne blocks this towards mid on.
Ravindra Jadeja gets turn straight away! Bowls this full and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne pushes at the ball and gets beaten in the outside edge.
Spin for the first time in this Test as Ravindra Jadeja is introduced into the attack.
Bowls an in-swinger once again from a good length and just outside off. Steven Smith blocks this out towards the mid on fielder.

Bowls this one short and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne pulls this towards mid-wicket and Ravindra Jadeja makes a good stop low to his left. They take a single as the ball is parried towards mid on.
Attacks the stumps once again on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne defends this back towards the bowler.
Goes full and angles this into the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne dabs this towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne blocks this one out solidly.

FOUR! Another outside edge and four more runs added to Marnus Labuschagne's kitty! Mohammed Siraj bowls this full and in line with the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne looks to block this with soft hands but gets a thick edge that flies into the gap towards third man for four runs.
Gets this one to nip back in sharply from a fuller length and just outside the off pole. Steven Smith is across the stumps once again but he just about manages to block this towards mid on.
A tad bit fuller and outside the off pole. Steven Smith steps across the line of the stumps and looks to play at the ball but decides to leave it at the last moment.
On a good length once again and outside the off stump. Steven Smith lets the keeper collect this one.

FOUR! First boundary for Steven Smith and it is a beautiful cover-drive! Mohammad Shami bowls this slightly fuller and outside the off stump. Steven Smith gets a good stride forward and strokes this towards deep cover for four runs.
Bowls this one wide outside the off pole on a good length. Steven Smith not interested to play at this one.
Mohammad Shami strays onto the pads on a fuller length. Steven Smith clips this towards deep backward square leg and collects a couple of runs to get off the mark.

What a jaffa! Mohammed Siraj bowls this on a good length and angles it into the batter but gets the ball to straighten after pitching. Marnus Labuschagne plays for the line of the ball and gets beaten on the outside edge,
Goes back to bowling on a good length and outside off. Marnus Labuschagne raises his arms to this one.

FOUR! Second boundary of the over and a bit of fortune in this one! Mohammed Siraj goes slightly fuller and outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne pushes at the ball and it takes the outside edge as it goes through the gap in the slip cordon for four runs to third man.
Continues to bowl on a good length and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne taps this into the pitch on the off side.
Bowls on a good length this time and outside the off pole. Marnus Labuschagne dabs this towards the point fielder.

FOUR! That is a controlled shot from Marnus Labuschagne as Australia get their first boundary off the bat! Mohammed Siraj bowls this full and in line with the stumps. Marnus Labuschagne punches this straight towards long on for four runs.
Bowls this on a good length as well and just outside the off pole. Steven Smith blocks this towards the mid on fielder. A maiden wicket for Mohammad Shami as well with just four byes conceded.
On a good length and angling into the batter, Steven Smith shuffles a bit to work it on the leg side. The ball keeps a bit low but Smith still manages to push it to mid-wicket.
There is definitely some wing on offer here! Mohammad Shami bowls this wide outside the off stump on a good length. Steven Smith leaves this one alone as well.
Shami serves this one fuller and swinging away outside off, Steven Smith does not reach out to the delivery and leaves it alone.

FOUR BYES! Mohammad Shami bowls this full and strays down leg. There is some late moevement in the air and the ball keeps going away from Srikar Bharat as he dives to his left. Four extra runs for Australia .
Steven Smith comes out to bat with Australia tottering at 2-2.

OUT! TIMBER! Mohammad Shami sends the stumps for a walk and both the Australian openers are back in the shed! Mohammad Shami bowls from 'round the wicket and serves this on a good length, angled into the stumps from outside off. David Warner gets forward slightly but plays the wrong line as the ball goes into the gap between the bat and the pad to send the off pole cart-wheeling away. Mohammad Shami and the Indian players look pumped up and this is just the start they were looking for. Australia are in a spot of bother here.
Offers width outside off once again on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne continues to raise his arm and leave the ball alone. A maiden wicket for Mohammed Siraj to start proceedings.
Beaten! That is a good delivery as he gets it closer to the off pole on a good length. Marnus Labuschagne feels for this one and the ball skims past the outside edge.
Continues to bowl on a good length and well outside off. Marnus Labuschagne shoulders his arms to this one as well.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Marnus Labuschagne leaves this one alone as the ball stays low once again.
On a good length outside off, Marnus Labuschagne shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
Marnus Labuschagne walks in at number 3 for Australia.

OUT! A huge wicket for India as the in-form Usman Khawaja has to depart! Mohammed Siraj draws first blood on his very first delivery and India are off to a good start! Massive shout! Mohammed Siraj bowls this full, on a leg stump line and gets the ball to shape back in. Usman Khawaja looks to clip this away but misses the line of the ball and plays all over this. A huge appeal from the Indian players around the bat. The umpire remains unmoved and after a delayed discussion Rohit Sharma goes upstairs for the review. UltraEdge shows there is no bat involved and Ball tracking shows three reds. The onfield decision has to be reversed and Australia lose their first wicket.
Mohammed Siraj will share the new ball from the other end.
Continues to bowl on the outside off-stump channel. David Warner will let the ball go through to the keeper once again.
Delivers this wide outside the off pole on a shorter length. David Warner raises his arms and leaves the ball alone.
Mohammad Shami comes 'round the wicket and serves this at the stumps on a good length. Usman Khawaja clips this towards square leg and takes one to open his account.
On a good length this time and just outside the off stump. Usman Khawaja shoulders his arms to this one as the ball stays low once again.

David Warner and Australia are off and running! Mohammad Shami bowls this back of a length and outside the off stump. David Warner gets on his toes and dabs this towards covers with soft hands. They take a quick single.
Mohammad Shami starts off with a fullish delivery but serves it wide outside the off stump. David Warner is watchful and leaves this one alone. Not much carry to the keeper.

Right then, we are done with the national anthems and we are all set for the action to start. Australian openers make their way out in the middle followed by the Indian players. David Warner and Usman Khawaja will open the innings for Australia. Mohammad Shami will start the proceedings with the new ball for India. Here we go...
Rohit Sharma and Pat Cummins lead their respective sides out for the national anthems. It will be Australia's first followed by the national anthem of India.

Mark Waugh is out in the middle for a live pitch report after the toss. He says that it is an unusual pitch with different shades on it. Mentions that it is dry but there is a nice grass covering. Admits that it is a big toss for Australians to win but they will need to be watchful while facing the new ball as there could be some help for the fast bowlers who will get some movement. Adds that they can make the most of it when the spinners come into the attack. Claims that the Australians will need to bat big in the first innings. Ends by saying that the spinners will need to bowl quick through the air, full and accurate.

Rohit Sharma says that they would have batted first as well but they have a quality bowling attack to restrict the opponents. Mentions that the pitch looks pretty dry and there will be some help for the bowlers, especially spinners. Claims that when they trained on this ground there was some movement for the seamers so they will see how they start. Adds that they have had good preparation over the last few days while training and the boys are looking forward to it. Admits that it is the big one and they know the importance of the series so they want to come and win every session without looking far ahead. ends by saying that they have three spinners and two pacers with two debutants.

Pat Cummins the captain of Australia says they will have a bat. Mentions that the pitch looks different from what they have in Australia. Claims that they all come to India a couple of times in a year and that should help them understand the conditions better. Reckons that they need to tweak a few things from how they played against South Africa. Adds that they have had good preparations over the last few months and they feel well placed. Admits that they have had a few injuries but have a big squad. Informs that they have two changes from their last game at Sydney.

India (Playing XI) - Rohit Sharma (C), KL Rahul, Cheteshwar Pujara, Virat Kohli, Suryakumar Yadav, Srikar Bharat (WK), Ravindra Jadeja, Ravichandran Ashwin, Axar Patel, Mohammad Shami, Mohammed Siraj.
Australia (Playing XI) - David Warner, Usman Khawaja, Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith, Matt Renshaw, Peter Handscomb, Alex Carey (WK), Pat Cummins (C), Todd Murphy, Nathan Lyon, Scott Boland.
TOSS - The captains are out in the middle. The coin is flipped into the air and lands in favor of Australia. They have elected to BAT first.

PITCH REPORT - Sanjay Manjrekar and Matthew Hayden are near the deck. Manjrekar says that the soil looks rough and there are cracks as well. Adds that the cracks may remain intact due to the grass. Shares that there is a rough patch for left-handed batters which could prove to be a nightmare for them. Hayden feels that this match might finish early. Mentions that there is a tone difference between the hard and good length. Reckons that this wicket is going to be a turner.

Two Indian players receive their Test cap as Srikar Bharat and Suryakumar Yadav are set to make their Test debuts. A great moment for the two lads and it can be witnessed by the beaming smiles on their faces. Srikar Bharat gets his cap from Cheteshwar Pujara and Suryakumar Yadav gets it from Ravi Shastri. The Australians have a debutant as well as Todd Murphy receives his baggy green from Nathan Lyon.

The afternoon session on the moving day is set to begin. The Indian players are seen to be in a huddle near the ropes, as the two umpires make their way out on the field. So, it was David Warner and Usman Khawaja who stride out with their swords. Followed by the Indian team who spread out after some positive words passed on by the skipper. It will be Mohammad Shami to start with the new ball.
... DAY 3, SESSION 2 ...

So, India clearly have their noses in front here. The Aussies certainly have their task cut out here with the deficit of 223 runs. In the first innings. Australia were bundled out for 177 runs. They surely need to bring their A-game this time. Do join us for the post-Lunch session at 12.10 pm IST (6.40 am GMT) to find out how things pan out.

Australian bowlers were made to toil hard more than they would have wanted. The seamers did not have much success in this deck which had some venom on it. The spinners though certainly feasted on this wicket. It was mainly a Todd Murphy show. The young debutant stood out with the ball with his seven-wicket haul. Murphy is certainly a fast learner. He took his time to read the conditions but once he got his first wicket, there was no stopping him. He kept on hitting right lines and lengths consistently which eventually made his outing a bit more special. Nathan Lyon though bowled really well but did not have his fair share of luck. He could only take a single scalp. Pat Cummins took a brace, while Boland rather had a difficult outing.

The Indian innings was well and truly led by their skipper, Rohit Sharma. The captain scored his first ever ton as a captian in Test match and his first against Australia. Although, India were looking in all sorts of trouble when they were teetering at 168 for 5. Lately though Indian batting order offers more depth than ever and that has come to their rescue once again. Ravindra Jadeja and Axar Patel stitched the highest partnership of the innings of 88 runs and both scored their respective half-centuries. Ravindra Jadeja fell out early in the morning session of the moving day, but Mohammad Shami did not even hesitate once to join the party. The seamer was dropped on 6 runs by Scott Boland and he managed to make the most of his reprieve as he slipped out for 37 runs. Later, Siraj came in and was very defensive with his approach which allowed Patel to free his arms but agonizingly fell short of his century.

Phew! An intriguing knock from Patel finally comes to an end. India have managed to score 79 runs for the final three wickets here. Australia might have been under the pump to bowl for 30 more minutes if Pat Cummins hadn't got rid of Axar Patel right at the cusp of Lunch. The away side would be much relieved.

OUT! BOWLED! Pat Cummins bowls a cutter, full on the off stump, Axar Patel goes for the slog on the leg side but gets deceived by the pace of the delivery. Fails to get any bat on it and sees the off bail dislodged. That brings an end to India's innings and they end up with 400 on the board. It will also be LUNCH on Day 3!
Back of a length around off by Pat Cummins, Axar Patel hangs back and dabs it to deep backward point. Decides not to take a single.
Cummins dishes a length ball, on off. Siraj runs it down to third man off the outside edge. One taken. Also, 400 is up for India. Who would've thought that?
Fuller, on off. Patel taps it to covers. Just a couple runs off it.
Short, outside off. Patel cuts it hard, but only to the man at covers.
Axar Patel gets on his front foot and blocks this full ball solidly.
Tosses it up, full and on middle. Patel helps it to mid on.
Full, on the pads, Patel comes forward and flicks it through mid on. The call is for two runs and Mohammed Siraj puts in a desperate dive at the non-striker's end to complete the two runs.
Slower through the air, full and on off. Defended back to the bowler.
Change of ends for Nathan Lyon now.
Fuller, on leg stump. Siraj hangs back and sees off another over as he flicks this one to mid-wicket.

A full toss, on off. Siraj defends it out to covers with soft hands.
Three dots to start with! Much fuller, outside off, shaping away this time. Siraj shuffles and tries to smack it through the line but misses.
Fuller, angled in on middle. Siraj stays back and defends it out watchfully.
Cummins starts with a length ball that nips in a touch off the deck. Siraj shuffles and flicks it to square leg.
Change. Finally, Pat Cummins gets himself back into the deck. He only bowled the first over of the moving day so far.

Patel knocks this full ball back to the bowler.
SIX! STRAIGHT HIT! Todd Murphy floats this one, slower and full on middle, Axar Patel shimmies down the track and gets to the pitch of the delivery. Lofts it over the bowler's head for a maximum.
Darted on the pads, tucked to square leg.

BYE! Floats it up, full and outside off. It grips and turns in. Siraj tries to drive it away but misses. Carey parries it away to the leg side. They collect a bye.

Short ball, outside off. Patel rocks back and cuts it to deep point for a single. Mohammad Siraj needs to eat up three balls here.

Todd Murphy gets his 7th wicket and Australia get a much-needed breakthrough.
Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Todd Murphy

Drinks break! India have extended their lead to 175 runs. Australia would've thought that they could have the innings in their pocket after getting rid of Ravindra Jadeja, but now this time it is the ninth-wicket stand that has started to frustrate then. Shami has faced 30 balls so far and scored 16 runs. To be honest he has been very comfortable so far. Australia would be hoping to strike early after this short break. Will the Indian batters continue on their merry way? Or does this break has an effect on their concentration? Let us find out.
