We are all set for the play to commence on Day 3. The umpires make their way out in the middle followed by the Australian players. Axar Patel and Ravindra Jadeja will resume the innings for India. Pat Cummins will start the proceedings with the ball for Australia. Here we go...

PITCH REPORT - Sanjay Manjrekar and Mark Waugh are near the deck. Waugh says that the main body of the pitch hasn't done anything at all but some cracks might start to open up and so batting might not be easy. Adds that there is a rough patch which the Australian left-handed batters have to deal with and they need to bat better. Ends by saying it is not going to be easy but Australia should be better equipped to handle it.

Australia failed to get an early breakthrough on Day 2, but Todd Murphy struck twice in the second hour of the first session. He added two more wickets to his tally and got his maiden five-wicket haul. Having reduced the hosts to 240-7 after tea, they were hopeful of wrapping up the Indian innings quickly but failed to do so. The visitors will look to pick the remaining three wickets soon and bat well in the second innings. It promises to be yet another exciting day of cricket. The action on Day 3 coming up shortly...

India survived the first hour without losing any wickets, but they were pegged back as they lost wickets on either side of the lunch break. Rohit Sharma looked in complete control on a tricky wicket and notched up a well-compiled hundred. Ravindra Jadeja and Axar Patel got together and stitched an unbeaten 81-run stand to hand the hosts a lead of 144 runs. The hosts would want this pair to bat as long as possible and build a huge lead.

Hello and a warm welcome, ladies and gentlemen, to our coverage of Day 3 of the first Test between India and Australia at the Vidarbha Cricket Association Stadium in Nagpur. Similar to Day 1, Day 2 was not short of action either, and it were the hosts who dominated the proceedings and were the happier side at Stumps.
... DAY 3, SESSION 1 …

Right then, India with the upper hand in this first Test match of the Border-Gavaskar Trophy and have taken a massive step towards winning this game on Day 2. Australia will have to play out of the skin to get themselves back into the tie but we have seen some outstanding turnarounds in this particular fixture. The battle will continue on Day 3 which is considered the moving day of Test cricket and we will be back on Saturday 11th February to see what ensues. The game will begin at 9.30 am IST (4 am GMT) but as you know do join us in advance for the build-up. Cheers!

Axar Patel is up for a quick chat. He says that he has been performing with the bat over the last year and he has taken that confidence into this game as he looks to perform when the team needs him. Feels that he has a good technique and he was focusing on working on his initial movement. Adds that Rahul Dravid and Vikram Rathour rate him highly and he has been working with them to improve. Shares that it is initially tough on this wicket and there are runs to be had once the batter gets set. Reckons that is important to not lose focus despite being set. When asked about their bowling plans on Day 3, he smiles and says that they need to focus on their batting first.

The visitors were unable to get an early breakthrough on Day 2 as Rohit Sharma and Ravichandran Ashwin built a nice partnership and scored quite freely. The latter departed after playing a good knock for a nightwatchman and Cheteshwar Pujara was dismissed playing an aggressive shot. Todd Murphy claimed both the wickets in the first session and India went into Lunch trailing by 26 runs. Australia got off to a stunning start in the second session as Todd dismissed Virat Kohli on the very first delivery of the afternoon session and Suryakumar fell prey to Nathan Lyon. Rohit Sharma continued to hold one end and reached his century as he was well supported by Ravindra Jadeja who is having a remarkable Test match so far. The visitors have toiled hard all through the day with Todd Murphy the pick of the bowlers claiming his maiden five-wicket haul on debut and they will be hoping that Day 3 will be much more productive for them as they look for a way to get back in this match.

SESSION SUMMARY - 95 runs, 34 overs, and 2 wickets. A wonderful session for India as they have swelled up the lead to 144 runs and are in complete control of the game. They will go into Day 3 with 3 wickets in hand and will look to continue accumulating the runs through the morning session. The hosts did not have an auspicious start to the post-Tea session as they lost their skipper Rohit Sharma on 120 in the first over after the break as he was knocked over by Pat Cummins with the new ball. Srikar Bharat looked to be proactive at the wicket but could not make the most of his opportunity but that was not the case with Axar Patel. He joined Ravindra Jadeja and the two southpaws began piling on the misery on the Australian bowlers. Both of them managed to get their half-centuries as they put on an unbeaten 81-run partnership for the eighth wicket but Australia will be disappointed with their catching in this game.
Tosses this one full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja takes a  big stride forward and smothers the ball. That will be STUMPS on Day 2!

DROPPED! Another reprieve for Ravindra Jadeja! Nathan Lyon bowls this one short and turning away outside off, Ravindra Jadeja hangs out his bat away from his body and gets an outside edge. The ball travels quickly to Steven Smith at first slip who reacts quickly low to his right but is unable to hold onto the sharp chance. Would have been huge for Australia to break this partnership just before Stumps.
Keeps it full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja gets on the front foot and works it towards point.
Flighted, full and on middle and leg, Ravindra Jadeja gets behind the line and defends it to short leg.
Goes full again and at the stumps from 'round the wicket, Ravindra Jadeja keeps this one out off the front foot.
Bowls this one full and at the middle stump, Ravindra Jadeja presses forward and defends it on the off side.
Fullish delivery at the pads, Axar Patel stays in the crease and keeps this one out. Last over of the day coming up.
Short and turning away outside off, Axar Patel dabs this one off the back foot to backward point.
Full and on middle by Todd Murphy, Axar Patel gets on the front foot and blocks it out.
Floats this one full and into the stumps. Axar Patel blocks this out into the off side.
Bowls this slightly short and outside off. Axar Patel rocks back and punches this towards cover.
Bowls it full and on off, Axar Patel defends this one down the wicket.
FOUR! Another full toss on middle by Matt Renshaw, Ravindra Jadeja clips this one along the ground and gets it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Low full toss at the batter, Ravindra Jadeja pushes it down to mid on.
Full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja keeps this one out off the front foot.
Full and angling at the pads, Axar Patel turns this one on the leg side and takes a single.
Another full toss on middle, Ravindra Jadeja drills it toward mid on where Pat Cummins dives to his left and keeps it to one.
Starts with a full toss on leg, Axar Patel pushes it to mid on for a single.
Full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja presses forward and defends it down the wicket.
Goes full on off, Ravindra Jadeja gets forward and blocks this one out.

FIFTY for Axar Patel! Short and around off by Todd Murphy, Axar Patel stays on the back foot and punches it down to long off for a single. This has been a remarkable inning as he came into the wicket with his team having lost a couple of wickets early in the session and his knock has taken the bite out of the Australian bowling attack.
Short and turning away on off, Axar Patel hangs back to defend but gets surprised by the sharp turn. The ball raps him on his gloves and luckily for him, the ball does not lob.
DROPPED! Short and on off, Ravindra Jadeja goes back in his crease to cut but gets an outside edge. Alex Carey fails to pouch the deflection and the ball lobs towards short third man for a single.
Full and drifting in on middle, Ravindra Jadeja gets forward and blocks this one out.

Slight halt! The Indian physios are out in the middle treating Axar Patel as he seems to have done something to his right arm. There is an ice pack on it at the moment and the players wait till he gets his treatment. He seems to be okay to continue now and we are all set to resume...
Short and on off, Axar Patel stays on the back foot and punches it to cover.
Fired in full and on off, Axar Patel works this one to silly-point.
Goes full again and around off, Axar Patel drives firmly but fails to get it past cover.
Short and angling in on middle, Axar Patel goes back and blocks this one out.
Floated, full outside off, Axar Patel plays with the turn and drives it to cover.
Starts with a full delivery outside off, Axar Patel presses forward and pushes it to cover.
Switches to over the wicket and bowls it short on off, Axar Patel punches it to long off for a single. Moves to 49 with this single.
Tossed up, full and at the stumps by Todd Murphy, Axar Patel gets on the front foot and keeps this one out.
Full and quicker on off, Axar Patel drives it a bit uppishly towards cover.
Tossed up, full and at the batter, Axar Patel presses forward and blocks it out.
Goes short again and at the pads, Axar Patel turns this one to short fine leg. Ravindra Jadeja wants a single but Axar Patel says no.
Starts with a short delivery on off, Axar Patel goes back and pushes it back to the bowler.
Fuller and at the pads, Ravindra Jadeja tries to work it on the leg side but gets a leading edge that falls wide of mid-wicket.
Flighted, full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja presses forward and defends this one down the wicket.
Full and around off, Axar Patel reaches out to the delivery and knocks it down to long off for a single.
Full and quicker at the batter, Axar Patel pushes it to the left of the bowler for a dot.
Floats, full on middle, Axar Patel gets forward and blocks this one out.
Bowls this one flat at the batter, Axar Patel gets behind the line and defends it on the leg side.
Fuller delivery at the pads, Ravindra Jadeja clips this one in front of square on the leg side and collects a couple of runs.
Slower and short on middle, Axar Patel plays it with the turn and knocks it to the right of mid-wicket for a single.
Switches to over the wicket and keeps it short and on leg, Axar Patel works this one to short leg.
Fullish delivery on off, Axar Patel pushes it down the wicket, Marnus Labuschagne dives to his left and saves a run.
Flighted, full and turning in on middle, Axar Patel keeps this one out off the front foot.
FOUR! Marnus Labuschagne misses his length and bowls a low full toss at the batter, Axar Patel needs no second invitation as he thumps this one well wide of long on for a boundary.
Fired in fraction short on off, Ravindra Jadeja gets hurried as he tried to cut and gets an inside edge.
Goes full and around off, Ravindra Jadeja gets on the front foot and blocks it out on the off side.
Floated, full on middle, Ravindra Jadeja presses forward and smothers the ball down the wicket.
Fullish delivery at the stumps, Ravindra Jadeja squeezes this one out to the left of the bowler.
Full and quicker around off, Ravindra Jadeja guides this one towards backward point.
Tossed up, full at the pads, Ravindra Jadeja pushes this one to mid-wicket.
Full and turning in on off, Axar Patel goes for the drive but gets an inside edge that rolls to short fine leg.
Flighted, full outside off, Ravindra Jadeja gets on the front foot and works it towards point for a single.
Short and turning into the batter, Ravindra Jadeja stays back and pushes it to mid-wicket.
Tossed up, full on middle, Ravindra Jadeja presses forward and blocks this one out.
Short and at the batter, Axar Patel swivels and pulls it towards deep square leg for a single.

FOUR! Axar Patel greets Marnus Labuschagne with a boundary! Bowls this one fraction short and turning in outside off, Axar Patel goes deep in his crease and guides this past Steven Smith at first slip for a boundary. 300 comes up for India.
Marnus Labuschagne (3-0-11-0) has been handed the ball now as Australia looking to change things up.
Keeps it full and on off, Axar Patel drives it with a straight bat to mid on and retains the strike with a single.

FOUR! Smart batting! Shorter in length outside off by Pat Cummins, Axar Patel allows the ball to come to him and uses the pace of the delivery. Steers this one along the ground through the slip cordon for a boundary.
On a good length outside off from 'round the wicket, Axar Patel punches it to backward point.
Another back-of-a-length delivery outside off, Axar Patel pushes this one off the back foot to cover.
Back of a length on off, Axar Patel stays on the back foot and defends it on the off side.
Bowls this one full and around off, Axar Patel drives this one nicely to mid off.
Fired in full and at the stumps, Ravindra Jadeja pushes this one down the wicket for a dot. 8th maiden of the game for Todd Murphy.
Tossed up, full and on leg, Ravindra Jadeja drives it along the ground towards mid on.
Darted in full and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja gets behind the line and blocks this one out.
Goes short and at the stumps, Ravindra Jadeja goes back and works it to cover.
Floated, full on middle and leg, Ravindra Jadeja pushes it to mid on for a dot.
Bowls it full and on off, Ravindra Jadeja gets forward and defends it on the off side.
Slight halt! The ground staff is out and flattening the patch at the bowler's landing area with a sledgehammer. We are all set to resume now...
On a length outside off by Pat Cummins, Axar Patel pushes this one off the back foot to cover.
Back of a length on off, Axar Patel stays back and dabs this one to backward point.
Full and on middle and leg, Axar Patel drives this one firmly to mid on.
FOUR! Nicely played! Pat Cummins bowls it full and on off, Axar Patel presents a straight bat and drives it back past the bowler. Gets it wide of mid on for a boundary. 50-run stand comes up.
Goes full and in the channel outside off, Axar Patel watchfully blocks this one out on the off side.
Starts with a shortish delivery outside off, Axar Patel hangs back and looks to punch it on the off side but miscues it towards mid on.
Pat Cummins (16-2-65-1) brings himself back into the attack.
Full and drifting in on middle, Ravindra Jadeja gets behind the line and defends it out.
Slower and a bit short around off, Ravindra Jadeja shoulders arms and lets it go.
Tosses this one full and around off, Ravindra Jadeja takes a stride forward and blocks it out on the off side.
Keeps it short and at the stumps, Ravindra Jadeja pushes it back to the bowler.
Short and into the batter, Ravindra Jadeja clips this one towards mid-wicket.
Goes short and outside off, Axar Patel rocks back and punches it to deep point for a single.
Pushed through quicker and short on middle, Ravindra Jadeja goes back in his crease and works it to cover. Axar Patel wants a single but gets sent back by Jadeja.
Flighted, full around off, Axar Patel presses forward and drives it down to long off for a single.
Short and at the stumps, Axar Patel taps this one off the back foot to cover.
Full and angling in on middle, Axar Patel leans forward and plays it back to the bowler.
Goes full and on middle, Axar Patel pushes it to mid on.
FOUR! Nathan Lyon it short again and outside off, Axar Patel cuts and cuts hard towards deep backward point. David Warner puts in a valiant effort but cannot prevent the boundary.

Slight halt! Ravindra Jadeja has taken permission from the umpires and Pat Cummins to momentarily leave the field. The players will take a drinks interval to save time with India in a dominating position having a lead of 105 runs and they will be hoping that the two batters out in the middle can continue to rack up the runs. Australia need to break this partnership and will want to wrap up the innings before Stumps.
Full and quicker on off, Ravindra Jadeja gets on the front foot and defends it on the off side.
Goes full again and on middle, Ravindra Jadeja gets forward and blocks it out.
Full and turning away outside off, Axar Patel pushes this one to cover for a single.
FOUR! A rare loose delivery by Todd Murphy, bowls it short and outside off, Axar Patel does not miss out as he cuts this one firmly through covers for a boundary.
Brave leave! Murphy bowls this one full and around off, Axar Patel presses forward and leaves the ball alone. It wasn't too far away from the off stump.
Bowls this one full and on off, Axar Patel pushes it to mid on.

FOUR! Short and put away by Ravindra Jadeja! Nathan Lyon shortens his length and bowls it outside off, Ravindra Jadeja rocks back in his crease and cuts it through covers. David Warner puts in the dive but the ball beats him to the fence.
Another full delivery on middle, Ravindra Jadeja gets behind the line and defends it on the leg side.
Flighted, full around off, Axar Patel plays with the turn and drives it wide of long off for a single.
Full and outside off, Axar Patel shoulders arms and leaves the ball alone.
Goes full and on middle, Axar Patel presents a straight bat and blocks this one out.
Short and turning away outside off, Axar Patel goes back in his crease and defends it on the off side.
Short and angling at the pads, Axar Patel works it to short fine leg and retains the strike with a single.
FOUR! Nicely played! Todd Murphy floats this one full and at the stumps, Axar Patel gets into the position early and drives it along the ground. Gets it to the right of mid off for a boundary.
Fired in full and on middle, Axar Patel presses forward and blocks it on the off side.
Short and around off, Axar Patel stays back and punches it to cover.
Slower and shorter on middle, Axar Patel goes back and defends this one down the wicket.
Bowls this one full and on leg, Axar Patel leans forward and works it to short leg.
Tosses this one full and into the pads. Ravindra Jadeja gets forward once again and blocks this to the left of the bowler.
Flighted full and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja gets his front foot forward and defends this into the off side.
Slightly short and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja slaps this towards deep point and collects a couple of runs.
Floats this one full and onto the pads. Ravindra Jadeja flicks this towards mid on.
Bowls this one slightly short and spinning into the stumps from outside leg. Ravindra Jadeja tucks this to short fine leg.
Nathan Lyon bowls from over the wicket and serves this full, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja leaves this one alone as the ball is spinning away further.

DRINKS! After losing two wickets in quick succession, Axar Patel and Ravindra Jadeja have steadied the ship and have taken India's lead to 88 runs. Jadeja brought up his fifty and needs to convert this fifty into a big one. On the other hand, Australia would have hoped to wrap up the innings quickly after dismissing Rohit Sharma and Srikar Bharat but have failed to do so. With India's lead closing in on the 100-run mark, the visitors need a breakthrough soon and get into the tail of the hosts.

FOUR! Outstanding shot and this has been placed to perfection! Scott Boland bowls this one full and outside the off stump. Axar Patel is looking to score runs now and goes for the booming cover drive. Gets this past the fielder and the ball runs away to the deep cover fence for four runs.

Bowls this one full and outside the off stump. Axar Patel looks to drive but is early into the shot as the ball gets stuck in the wicket. He goes through with the shot and gets it over the infield for a couple of runs to deep cover.
Goes full this time and strays down leg. Ravindra Jadeja flicks this towards deep backward square leg and collects an easy single.
Delivers this one wide outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja is watchful this time and he leaves this one alone.
Angles this into the stumps on a good length. Axar Patel gets this off the outside half of his bat to the right of point for a run.
Scott Boland bowls this a tad bit full and outside the off pole. Axar Patel lets this one go through to the keeper.
Another tossed-up delivery served full and outside off. Ravindra Jadeja taps this towards point.
Flighted full and into the stumps. Ravindra Jadeja uses his wrist and clips this towards square leg.
A loopy delivery bowled into the pads. Ravindra Jadeja digs this out towards mid on.
Flights this one in line with the stumps on a fuller length. Ravindra Jadeja blocks this back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Tosses this one full and into the stumps. Ravindra Jadeja dabs this watchfully towards point.
Nathan Lyon floats this one full and into the pads. Ravindra Jadeja flicks this towards square leg.
Angles this one down leg. Axar Patel leaves this one alone and Alex Carey does well to collect the ball behind the wicket by diving to his right.
Bowls this one full and strays onto the pads. Axar Patel flicks this straight to mid-wicket.

That is FIFTY for Ravindra Jadeja, and what an amazing game he is having! Scott Boland bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja taps this towards cover-point and takes a single. He does his trademark celebration as he wields his blade.
Goes full this time and onto the pads. Axar Patel flicks this towards deep square leg for a single.
On a good length once again and outside the off pole. Axar Patel is not interested in playing at this one as well.
Scott Boland bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Axar Patel shoulders his arms and lets the keeper collect the ball.
Slight halt! Scott Boland has some issues with the landing area and wants repair work to be done there. The ground staff have evened out that area and play will resume now.
Steep bounce this time! Nathan Lyon bowls this on a shorter length and outside off. Ravindra Jadeja goes forward but has to back away as the ball leaps off the surface.
Bowls this one short and into the stumps. Axar Patel goes on the back foot and punches this down to long off for a run.
Gets the edge this time! Tosses this full and outside off. Axar Patel looks to block but gets an outside edge that falls just short of slip.
Bowls this full and on the pads. Ravindra Jadeja plays this towards deep square leg and they run brilliantly to complete three runs.
Beaten once again! Nathan Lyon gives air to the ball and flights this full, outside off. Sharp turn and bounce off the wicket and Ravindra Jadeja is beaten on the outside edge.
Nathan Lyon gets this one to turn sharply! Floats this full and just outside the off pole. Ravindra Jadeja pushes forward but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Ends the over with a full delivery on the pads. Axar Patel eases this towards the fielder at mid on.
Bowls this on a good length as well and outside the off stumps. Axar Patel is happy to raise his arms and lets this go through to the keeper.
On a good length this time and wide outside off. Axar Patel stands tall and pushes this towards cover-point.

Just short of the slip fielder! Scott Boland bowls this full and into the stumps. Axar Patel looks to whip this leg side but ends up geat a leading edge that falls just short of Steven Smith at second slip.
On a good length once again and outside the off pole. Ravindra Jadeja punches this towards deep point for a single.
Scott Boland begins from 'round the wicket and bowls this on a good length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja knocks this straight to mid off.
Scott Boland (14-4-23-0) comes back into the attack.
Continues to bowl full and on a leg stump line. Axar Patel taps this into the pitch to play out another maiden over.
Nathan Lyon flights this full and in line with the stumps. Axar Patel defends this back towards the bowler.
Loops this one full and outside the off stump. Axar Patel blocks this one out.
Goes full once again and offers width outside off. Axar Patel strokes this but cant beat the man at cover.
Bowls this short and outside the off stump. Axar Patel rocks back and punches this towards the cover-fielder.
Nathan Lyon floats this one full and into the stumps from outside off. Axar Patel blocks this out into the off side.
Gets this one to jag back in sharply. Ravindra Jadeja gets cramped for room and gets hit high on the thigh pad.
Continues to bowl full and outside off. Ravindra Jadeja is watchful as he pushes this towards mid off.
Bowls this one on a fuller length and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja shoulders his arms to this one.
Bowls this back of a length and going down leg. Axar Patel gets on his toes and tucks this towards deep square leg for a single. Brings up the 250 for India!
Goes full and into the pads. Axar Patel digs this out back down the pitch towards the bowler.
Pat Cummins bowls this full and just outside the off pole. Axar Patel defends this solidly towards mid off.
Bowls this one in line with the stumps on a fuller length. Ravindra Jadeja gets forward well and taps this down the pitch. A maiden over for Todd Murphy.
Bowls this quicker in the air and into the pads on a fuller length. Ravindra Jadeja gets his bat down in time and knocks this towards mid on.
Tosses this one full and into the pads. Ravindra Jadeja clears his front foot and dans this into the off side.
Flighted full and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja blocks this into the pitch on the off side.
Loops this one full and into the pads. Ravindra Jadeja defends this to the right of the bowler.
Todd Murphy floats this one full and into the pads. Ravindra Jadeja pushes this towards cover-point and looks for a single that is not there.
Bowls this one slightly short as well and on an off-stump line. Axar Patel is well behind this one as he blocks this towards cover.
Angles this in from outside off and gets it to straighten after pitching from back of a length. Axar Patel feels for this one but is nowhere near the ball.
Goes full this time and into the stumps. Ravindra Jadeja knocks this down the ground to the right of mid on for a single.
Slightly short once again and bowled into the batter. Ravindra Jadeja gets on his toes and dabs it to the left of the pitch.
Delivers this on a good length and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja hangs his bat out to dry and gets beaten all ends up.
Pat Cummins bowls this back of a length and onto the pads. Ravindra Jadeja tucks this towards deep square leg and takes two runs.
Flighted full and outside the off pole. Axar Patel pushes this towards mid off.
Goes full and going down leg. Axar Patel flicks this towards mid-wicket and cannot take a run.
Bowls this one short and outside the off stump. Cuts this one hard but cant beat the extra cover fielder.
Flighted full and on the middle-stump line. Axar Patel clips this towards mid on.
Floats this one full and into the stumps. Axar Patel blocks this towards point and looks for one before sending Ravindra Jadeja back.
Todd Murphy angles this into the pads on a shorter length. Axar Patel goes back in the crease and keeps this out.
Angles this in from outside off on a good length. Ravindra Jadeja knocks this firmly towards cover.
Continues to bowl on a good length and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja leaves this on alone.
On a good length once again and outside the off pole. Ravindra Jadeja defends this solidly into the off side.
Beaten! Bowls this back of a length and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja looks to play at it and gets beaten on the outside edge.

This is bowled on a good length and just outside the off pole. Ravindra Jadeja is on the back foot and looks to block the ball away. Another huge appeal, and Pat Cummins this time discusses with his keeper and goes upstairs. Replays show that the bat hits the pad as he looks to play the shot and the ball makes an impact on the pad before hitting the bat. Ball Tracking shows that the impact is the umpire's call once again and Ravindra Jadeja continues to survive. Australia retain their review though.

FOUR! This is all about the timing! Pat Cummins bowls this on a good length and just outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja just leans into the shot and punches this straight down the ground towards long off for four runs.
Bowls this one short as well and wide outside off. Ravindra Jadeja cuts this towards point and sets off for a risky single.
Fires this on quick and into the [ads on a shorter length. Axar Patel tucks this towards square leg and gets off the mark with a single.
Loopy delivery bowled full and into the pads. Axar Patel knocks this uppishly towards mid on.
Tosses this one full and in line with the stumps. Axar Patel defends this back towards the bowler.
Todd Murphy floats this one full and into the stumps. Axar Patel blocks this out into the off side.
Axar Patel is the new man in.

PLUMB! Another excellent review from Australia! Todd Murphy gets his maiden five-wicket haul in his debut game and sends the Indian debutant packing! The bowler flights this one full and in line with the stumps. Srikar Bharat gets forward to block and gets hit on the pads. A massive appeal once again and Alex Carey convinces Pat Cummins to go upstairs for the review. UltraEdge confirms that there is no bat involved and Ball Tracking shows three reds. The on-field decision has to be overturned and India lose their seventh wicket. The Australians look absolutely thrilled as they are celebrating with the young bowler on his massive achievement.
Continues to bowl on a good length and gets it to nip back into the stumps. Srikar Bharat plays this with soft hands towards point and takes one to keep strike.
On a good length once again and outside the off pole. Ravindra Jadeja knocks this towards cover-point and crosses for a run.
Angles this into the stumps on a good length. Srikar Bharat taps this towards mid on and sets off for a sharp single.
Delivers this one slightly fuller and just outside the off pole. Srikar Bharat defends this solidly towards mid on.
Bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja dabs this towards deep point for a single.
Pat Cummins bowls from 'round the wicket and delivers this on a good length, outside off. Ravindra Jadeja defends this towards the cover fielder.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Srikar Bharat pushes this to the left of the bowler.

FOUR! That is a confident shot from the debutant! Todd Murphy tosses this one full and outside the off stump. Srikar Bharat gets down on his knees and sweeps this towards deep square leg for his first boundary in his international career.
Flighted full and outside the off stump. Srikar Bharat pushes this towards deep backward square leg for a couple of runs to score his first runs in Test cricket.
Fires this one full and into the pads. Srikar Bharat flicks this towards the square leg fielder.
Bowls this one short and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja dabs this towards point and sets off for a single.
Todd Murphy floats this one full and into the stumps. Ravindra Jadeja gets forward and blocks this into the off side.
Todd Murphy will share the second new ball from the other end.
On a good length and angled into the pads. Srikar Bharat clips this towards mid-wicket.
Cummins goes full but swinging down the leg side, Srikar Bharat misses the clip and Alex Carey behind the wicket dives quickly to his left and makes a good stop.
The debutant Srikar Bharat comes out to bat.

OUT! TIMBER! Pat Cummins decides to do it himself and Steven Smith will be the most relieved man on the field! This is an absolute ripper by the Australian captain as he sends his counterpart back to the shed. Delivers this on a good length and on an off stump line. Rohit Sharma looks to play for the line of the ball but it straightens after pitching and pegs the off pole back. Rohit Sharma looks back in disbelief and his outstanding inning comes to an end. India have lost their sixth wicket now and Australia will be hoping to wrap up this inning soon now. Pat Cummins gets his first wicket and the visitors get a wicket early after a break once again.

DROPPED! What a massive let-off for Rohit Sharma! Australia will be distraught as they had a golden opportunity to dismiss the set Indian captain. Pat Cummins bowls this full and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma looks to drive and gets an outside edge to the slip fielder. Steven Smith gets low to his right but the ball hits his wrists and goes through for a couple of runs.
Goes a touch fuller this time and angles this into the stumps. Rohit Sharma clips this towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this one on a good length and in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma blocks this with a straight bat back down the pitch.
NO BALL! Pat Cummins starts with a full delivery outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma dabs this wide of mid off. The bowler oversteps and the umpire indicates that it is a no ball.

We are back for the post-tea session on Day 2. The Australian players are seen in a huddle near the ropes and they now make their way out in the middle. Rohit Sharma and Ravindra Jadeja stride out to the centre to resume their innings. The second new ball is now available and Australia have taken it straight away. It will be Pat Cummins to start the proceedings in the third session. Let's play...
... DAY 2, SESSION 3 ...

Having pulled things back in the second hour of the first session, Australia were off to a perfect start in the second session. It was first Todd Murphy who struck on the first ball of the second session to get his fourth wicket and then Nathon Lyon got on the wickets column. However, after those two wickets, the visitors failed to pick up any more wickets in the session. Todd Murphy did come close to making Ravindra Jadeja his fifth victim only for it to be deemed umpire's call on impact. The visitors brought on Marnus Labuschagne to make use of the rough areas on the wicket but he failed to make a mark in his three overs. Don't go anywhere as we will be back shortly for the post-tea session at 2.30 pm IST (9 am GMT).

Session Summary - 75 runs, 28 overs and 2 wickets. Despite the early blip, the second session belonged to the hosts and they will be the happier side going into the Tea break. India resumed the post-lunch session with two of their most experienced players Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli out in the middle. However, the latter departed with the hosts still 26 runs away from taking the lead. The debutant Suryakumar Yadav got off the mark in Test cricket with a boundary but departed after scoring only 8 runs. Rohit Sharma looked in complete control on a tricky wicket notching up a well-compiled hundred. His unbeaten 58-run stand with Ravindra Jadeja has handed India a lead of 49 runs going into the break.
Floats this one into the pads on a fuller length. Ravindra Jadeja flicks this towards mid-wicket and the umpires indicate that it will be TEA on DAY 2.
Fires this one full and into the stumps. Ravindra Jadeja blocks this one into the off side.
This is slightly short and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja punches this towards the point fielder.
Flighted full and into the pads. Ravindra Jadeja dabs this down into the pitch on the leg side.
Angles this into the stumps on a shorter length. Ravindra Jadeja tucks this towards mid-wicket.
Loopy delivery bowled full and into the pads. Ravindra Jadeja goes deep in the crease and keeps this one out.
Tosses this one full as well and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma mistimes his drive straight to the cover fielder.
Flighted delivery bowled full and wide outside off. Rohit Sharma chooses to leave this one alone.
Continues to bowl full and this is served on the pads. Ravindra Jadeja eases this down to long on for a single.
Tosses this one full and just outside off. Ravindra Jadeja defends this one solidly.
Marnus Labuschagne flights this full and going down leg. Ravindra Jadeja misses his flick and the ball does onto hit the pads. Another appeal but the umpire remains unmoved. No review this time.
Marnus Labuschagne fires this one full and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma pushes this towards deep cover-point for a single.
Loopy delivery bowled full and just outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja gets well forward once again and blocks this back down the pitch.

Bowls this one full and into the stumps. Ravindra Jadeja gets a stride forward and clocks this out. Huge appeal from the bowler and he feels it is pad first. Pat Cummins opts for the review and we will go upstairs to check. Replays show the bat is really close to the pad but the third umpire reckons that the ball hits the pad first. Ball Tracking shows the impact is umpire's call and the onfield decision remains. Ravindra Jadeja survives a really close call and Australia retain their review.
Flights this one full and in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma shimmies down the wicket and clips this towards the mid-wicket region for a single.
Bowls this one slightly quicker outside off on a fuller length. Rohit Sharma dabs this into the off side.
Tosses this one full and in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma defends this to the right of the bowler.
Todd Murphy floats this full and into the pads. Rohit Sharma dabs this towards short leg.

FOUR! Ravindra Jadeja does not miss out this time! Marnus Labuschagne bowls this short and outside the off stump and it is easy picking for the batter. This is slapped away towards deep point for four runs and India building a really nice partnership here.
Bowls this one slightly short and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma dabs this towards point and takes one.
Continues to bowl full and outside the off pole. Rohit Sharma mistimes his shot straight to cover.
Tosses this one full and on an off stump line. Rohit Sharma keeps this one out.
Flights this one full and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja pushes at this and gets an outside edge towards the third man region for a single. Brings up the 50-run partnership.
Marnus Labuschagne bowls a high full toss and Ravindra Jadeja is unable to put this one away. Slaps this straight to mid-wicket.
Delivers this one full as well and just outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma flicks this straight to the mid-wicket fielder.
Todd Murphy goes over the wicket now and floats this full, into the stumps. Rohit Sharma shuffles forward and looks to work this leg side but gets a leading edge towards point.
Loops this one as well and bowls this outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma defends this towards cover.
Tosses this one full and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma blocks this into the off side.
FOUR! Clear intent shown by Rohit Sharma! Todd Murphy flights this full and straight. Rohit Sharma is down the wicket once again as he clips this into the gap towards deep mid-wicket for four runs.
Todd Murphy floats this one full and in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma shimmies down and digs this out back towards the bowler.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja gets a long stride forward and smothers this into the pitch.
Bowls this one short and in line with the stumps, much slower in the air. Rohit Sharma sits in the crease and tucks this towards deep mid-wicket for a run.
Floats this one onto the pads on a fuller length. Ravindra Jadeja flicks this towards deep backward square leg for one.
Flights this one full and on an off-stump line. Ravindra Jadeja pushes this towards mid off.
Slightly short and outside the off pole. Rohit Sharma dabs this towards point and sets off for a quick single.
Marnus Labuschagne starts off with a full delivery in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma defends this watchfully into the off side.
Marnus Labuschagne is introduced into the attack.

Goes full and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja gets a confident stride forward and defends this towards the cover fielder. He is looking really solid in his defense here barring the one edge through slips.
On a good length and attacks the stumps from 'round the wicket. Ravindra Jadeja is well behind the line of the ball as he blocks this back towards the bowler.

Bowls this one on a fuller length and outside the off stump. Ravindra Jadeja dabs this towards point.

Scott Boland goes 'round the wicket to the left-hander and bowls this full outside off. Ravindra Jadeja reaches for this and knocks this towards point.

OUT! CAUGHT BEHIND! Virat Kohli departs the first ball after Lunch! Todd Murphy is having a memorable debut here as he now gets his fourth wicket. Commentary.Howout: c Alex Carey b Todd Murphy

Commentary.Commentary: We are back for the afternoon session of Day 2 and the umpires are out in the middle. The Australian players disperse onto the field as Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli stride out to the center patch. Todd Murphy has been handed the ball and will continue his impressive performance after the break. Let's go...
... DAY 2, SESSION 2 ...

Australia would have been looking for a few wickets early in the session but their bowling attack looked quite blunt and were allowing runs to flow quite freely. They put the brakes on the scoring in the second hour of play and that began to build some pressure. Todd Murphy was the pick of the bowlers as he claimed the two wickets that fell in the morning session and now has taken all three wickets for his side. He has been really impressive on his debut and has caused some discomfort to the batters. Nathan Lyon has not been as effective and Australia will need to continue staying disciplined if they are to chip at the wickets and run through a strong batting lineup. A crucial afternoon session awaits us so do join us at 12.10 pm IST (6.40 am GMT) for more enticing action.

Session Summary - 74 runs, 28 overs, and 2 wickets. India have been able to tighten their grip over this game and now trail the visitors by just 26 runs with 7 wickets in hand. Rohit Sharma has played a skipper’s knock so far as he has managed to bat through the session and along with Ravichandran Ashwin got India off to a great start this morning as they added 42 runs for the second wicket. The nightwatchman departed on 23 having faced 62 deliveries and was replaced by Cheteshwar Pujara who came out with positive intent. He got off the mark on the very first delivery which is a rarity in itself and looked to play his shots but that brought about his downfall as he played one shot too many. Virat Kohli has joined Rohit Sharma in the middle and they will now look to take India to a healthy first-inning lead.

Keeps it on a length and at the stumps, Rohit Sharma steps out to defend but the ball spins sharply and hits him on the front pad. A polite enquiry by the Australians but it was turning down the leg side. That will be Lunch on Day 2!

Flatter and on off, Rohit Sharma steps out and defends it on the off side.
Bowls this one full and on middle, Rohit Sharma blocks this one out to short leg.
Short and at the stumps, the ball keeps low, and Virat Kohli somehow manages to push this on the leg side.
Nathan Lyon bowls this one full on off, Virat Kohli works it towards mid-wicket and looks for a single. A yes-no situation in the middle but Rohit Sharma gets sent back just in time.
Keeps it full again on off, Virat Kohli clips it to mid-wicket.
Pushed through straight, full outside off, Virat Kohli plays for the turn but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Tossed up, full and around off, Virat Kohli takes a stride forward and defends it towards cover.
Flighted, fuller on off, Virat Kohli gets forward and blocks this one out on the off side.
Another short delivery on middle, Virat Kohli looks to turn it on the leg side but the ball keeps low and Kohli gets an leading edge towards point for a single.
Short and quicker on middle, Virat Kohli goes on the back foot and keeps this one out.
FOUR! Virat Kohli is up and running! Todd Murphy overpitches a fraction on off, Virat Kohli takes a big stride forward and drives it to the right of mid off. Opens his account with a boundary.
Short and at the stumps, Virat Kohli goes back and works it to short leg.
Full and quicker on off, Virat Kohli leans to defend but gets it from the outer part of the bat towards point.
Pushed straight, full around off, Virat Kohli presses forward to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Floats this one full and into the stumps. Rohit Sharma flicks this towards mid-wicket
Flatter and quicker on middle and leg, Rohit Sharma tries to defend but the ball spins past his outside edge. Gets hit high on the pads and the ball lobs to short leg.
Tossed up, full on middle, Rohit Sharma gets forward and defends it on the leg side.
Flighted delivery, full around off, Rohit Sharma presses forward to defend but gets a thickish outside. It goes through short third man for a couple of runs.
Fuller on off from 'round the wicket, Rohit Sharma pushes this one back to the bowler.
Nathan Lyon flights this one full and on an off stump line. Rohit Sharma dabs this into the leg side.

Goes over the wicket now and floats it full on off, Virat Kohli presses forward and defends it back to the bowler. A wicket-maiden for Todd Murphy and this has been a remarkable effort by the debutant so far.
Short and on middle, Virat Kohli goes back and works it to short leg.
Fuller and on middle, Virat Kohli gets forward and clips this one straight to mid-wicket.
Another full delivery at the stumps, Virat Kohli leans forward and plays it back to Todd Murphy.
Bowls this one full and on middle, Virat Kohli solidly blocks this one out off the front foot.
Virat Kohli makes his way out to the middle and the crowd is going absolutely berserk. Chants of 'Kohli" all around the ground.

OUT! IN THE AIR AND GONE! Todd Murphy has his third wicket now and this time it's Cheteshwar Pujara! Todd Murphy bowls this one a bit fuller but down the leg side, Cheteshwar Pujara is tempted by the line of the delivery and looks to help it fine on the leg side but gets a top edge that goes towards short fine leg. Scott Boland stationed there makes no mistake. Australia are delighted as they should be.
Commentary.Howout: c Scott Boland b Todd Murphy

Commentary.Commentary: Boland keeps it on a length and straight at the stumps, Rohit Sharma clips this one firmly towards mid-wicket.
Full and around off by Scott Boland, Rohit Sharma defends this one from the front foot back to the bowler.
On a length outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara opens the bat face and steers this one wide of backward point for a single.
Goes full this time, on off, Cheteshwar Pujara goes on the front foot and defends it on the off side.
Back of a length outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara punches but gets it from the toe end of the bat towards cover.
Good length outside off, Cheteshwar Pujara opts not to reach out to the delivery and leaves it alone.
FOUR! Murphy fires this one full and quicker at the pads, Rohit Sharma allows the ball to come to him and uses the pace of the delivery. Turns this one past short fine leg for a boundary.
Tossed up, full on middle, Rohit Sharma gets forward and blocks this one out down the wicket.
Another full delivery outside off, Rohit Sharma presses forward and defends it on the off side.
Fullish delivery on off, Rohit Sharma digs this one out to mid off.

A huge appeal! Todd Murphy bowls this one full and on leg, Rohit Sharma takes a stride forward and looks to turn this one on the leg side but fails to get any bat on it. The ball lobs off his pads towards first slip where Steven Smith takes a good catch diving to his right. Australia think they have got their man and they decide to send it upstairs. However, the UltraEdge confirms that there was no bat and the Ball Tracking shows that the ball was pitching outside leg.
FOUR! Todd Murphy floats this one full and at the pads, Rohit Sharma does not miss out and clips this one nicely along the ground. Gets it through mid-wicket and collects a boundary.
Full and swinging in off, Cheteshwar Pujara works this one from the front foot to mid on.

A loud appeal but turned down! Scott Boland serves this one on a good length around off, the ball nips back in after pitching, Cheteshwar Pujara takes a stride forward to defend but gets an inside edge onto his pad. Alex Carey, Pat Cummins and Scott Boland get together but they decide not to review.
Length delivery, slanting in on off, Cheteshwar Pujara accounts for the movement and blocks this one out down the wicket.
Shorter in length on off, Cheteshwar Pujara stays back and defends it back to the bowler.
Bye! Boland strays down the leg side on a length, Rohit Sharma misses the flick and Alex Carey behind the wicket fails to collect it cleanly. Batters cross for a single.
NO BALL! On a good length, angling in on middle, Rohit Sharma gets behind the line and blocks it down the wicket.
Back of a length outside off by Scott Boland, Rohit Sharma stays back and punches it to mid off.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside the off stump. Cheteshwar Pujara is down the wicket this time but knocks it back towards the bowler. A successful over for Australia.

FOUR! Cheteshwar Pujara has played a shot on every delivery so far and has come out with positive intent! Todd Murphy bowls this short and outside off. Cheteshwar Pujara uses the depth of the crease well and cuts this towards deep cover-point for a cracking boundary.
Fights this one full and on the pads. Cheteshwar Pujara clips this towards mid-wicket.
Bowls this one shot and outside the off stump. Cheteshwar Pujara goes on the back foot and slaps this towards cover.
Cheteshwar Pujara opens his account straight away! Todd Murphy floats this one full and on the pads. Cheteshwar Pujara clips this towards deep square leg and takes a couple of runs.
Cheteshwar Pujara comes in at number 4.

LBW! Todd Murphy gets the breakthrough and it is a great review by Australia! Alex Carey was convinced behind the wicket that this is out and he is the one who pushes for the review. The bowler flights this one full and on a leg stump line. Ravichandran Ashwin gets forward to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. A huge appeal by the Australian players around the bat but the umpire remains unmoved. They huddle together to discuss and go upstairs for the review. UltraEdge confirms that there is no bat involved as the ball hit the pads straight. Ball Tracking shows three reds and the onfield decision has to be reversed. Ravichandran Ashwin has done a good job playing out most of the morning session but Australia really needed this wicket and they will look to take off from here.
Delivers this one wide outside off stump on a good length. Rohit Sharma hangs his bat out and the ball zips through to the keeper.
Starys down leg side this time on a good length. Ravichandran Ashwin clips this towards deep square leg for a single.
Continues bowling on a good length and outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin covers the line of the ball and defends this towards mid off.
On a good length this time and outside the off pole. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes this towards the fielder at cover.
Slightly back of a length this time and in line with the stumps. Ravichandran Ashwin stands tall and dabs this towards short mid-wicket.
Scott Boland bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks this solidly towards cover.

DRINKS! India have added 40 runs to their overnight score in the first hour and they now trail by 60 runs. Rohit Sharma and Ravichandran Ashwin have looked at ease out in the middle but need to carry on. Despite not getting a breakthrough in this passage of play, Australia have done well to dry up the runs in the last five overs.
Todd Murphy gets a maiden to keep the pressure on India. Tosses this one full and just outside the off pole. Rohit Sharma is watchful as he taps it towards short mid-wicket.
Continues to bowl full and into the stumps. Rohit Sharma shimmies down the wicket and knocks this back towards the bowler.
Loopy delivery bowled on a leg stump line. Rohit Sharma defends this towards short mid-wicket.
Tosses this one full and outside the off pole. Rohit Sharma dabs this into the off side.
Flights this one full and on the pads. Rohit Sharma clips this to the right of mid-wicket and avoids taking the single.
Todd Murphy floats this one full and in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma blocks this back towards the bowler.
Todd Murphy returns to the attack.

Yet another maiden for Scott Boland as he is helping Australia tighten the screws here. Bowls this one wide outside off on a fuller length. Ravichandran Ashwin reaches for the ball but is unable to time is shot and gets it to the cover fielder.
Goes a tad bit fuller this time and serves this outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin punches this towards cover.
Gets this one to angle into the stumps on a good length. Ravichandran Ashwin clips this towards mid-wicket.
Delivers this outside the off pole on a good length. Ravichandran Ashwin feels for this one and gets beaten all ends up.
Bowls this on a good length as well and outside off with the wicket-keeper standing at the stumps. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks this solidly towards cover.
Scott Boland bowls this on a good length and just outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin dabs this towards mid-wicket.
Loops this one full and into the pads. Rohit Sharma clips this towards the fielder at short mid-wicket. This partnership is building nicely for India.
Continues to flight and bowls it full, in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma well forward to dabs this back down the pitch.
Tosses this one full and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma blocks this slightly uppishly back towards the bowler.
Loopy delivery bowled full and outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin gets well forward and gets the off the outside half of his bat towards point for a quick single.
Flights this one full and on the pads. Rohit Sharma clips this to deep backward square leg and takes a single.
Nathan Lyon bowls this full and outside off. Rohit Sharma stays deep in the crease and blocks this into the off side.
Two maidens in a row for Scott Boland in this spell. Continues to bowl on a good length and on the outside off-stump channel. Ravichandran Ashwin defends this back towards the bowler.
Goes slightly fuller this time and outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin knocks this to the mid off fielder.
On a good length once again and outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin gets an inside edge into the leg side.
Gets this one to shape back in from outside off and serves this slightly short. Ravichandran Ashwin stands tall and looks to punch this away bit does not time it well.
Continues to bowl on a good length and outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes this towards mid off.
Scott Boland bowls this on a good length and outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin knocks this on the up towards the cover fielder.
FOUR! A bit of luck going India's way as well! Nathan Lyon loops this full and outside off. Rohit Sharma looks to work this leg side but gets a leading edge down to thrid man for four runs.
Flighted delivery once again bowled outside off. Rohit Sharma down the wicket once more but defends this into the off side.
Continues to bowl full and on a leg stump line. Rohit Sharma looks to get forward but ends up clipping this towards mid-wicket.
Tosses this one full and straight. Rohit Sharma taps this down towards short leg.
Flighted full and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma shimmies down the wicket and pushes this towards mid off.
Nathan Lyon loops this one full and in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma gets forward and dabs this into the leg side.
Bowls this one full and on off, Ravichandran Ashwin gets on the front foot and drives it back to the bowler.
Goes full and outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes  this towards mid off.
Slightly fuller and angles into the stumps on a good length. Ravichandran Ashwin clips this towards mid-wicket.
On a good length this time and outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin taps this towards mid on.
Bowls this one full and outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks this towards cover.

Scott Boland starts off with a good-length delivery that nips back in sharply from just outside off. Rohit Sharma looks to clip this leg side but gets cramped for room and gets hit on the pads. A stifled appeal by the bowler but nothing comes from it. They take a leg bye as the ball rolls towards backward point.
Scott Boland comes into the attack now.
Loopy delivery bowled full and on a leg stump line. Rohit Sharma eases this down to long on for one and will keep strike.
Bowls this slightly short and in line with the stumps from 'round the wicket. Rohit Sharma sits in the crease and blocks this one out.
Floats this one full and into the pads. Ravichandran Ashwin clips this towards deep square leg for a single.
Tosses this full and outside the off pole. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes this into the off side.

SIX! That sounded meaty as soon as Ravichandran Ashwin made contact with the ball! Nathan Lyon flights this full and outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin gets on his knees and slog sweeps this over deep mid-wicket for a maximum.
Nathan Lyon goes over the wicket and floats this one full and outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks this out in the off side.

SIX! Just over the fielder! Pat Cummins bangs this in short and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma gets into position in a flash and pulls this over the deep square leg fielder for a maximum. This shot came out of nowhere and is also been Rohit Sharma's kryptonite in the past. Executes it well this time though. This six brings up the 100 for India.
Goes full and outside the off pole. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to go for the expansive drive and miscues his shot wide of mid on. They rush across for a single.
Bowls this one slightly back of a length and going down leg. Ravichandran Ashwin is watchful as he raises his arms and lets the keeper collect the ball.
Delivers this outside the off pole on a good length. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to drive on the up but miscues his shot back towards the bowler.
Continues to bowl on a good length and just outside the off pole. Ravichandran Ashwin gets across the stumps and defends this to mid on.
Pat Cummins bowls this on a good length but strays onto the pads. Ravichandran Ashwin clips this straight to the square leg fielder.
Loops this one full and spinning down leg from middle. Rohit Sharma looks to lean forward and gets beaten by the turn to get hit on the pads.

Flights this one full and just outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes at this and gets an outside edge towards point. Rohit Sharma calls him through for a single but Ravichandran Ashwin is late to respond. Makes it across in time.
Continues to bowl full and outside the leg stump. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes this to the right of the bowler.
Flights this full and straight. Ravichandran Ashwin dabs this back down the pitch.
Goes full and into the pads. Ravichandran Ashwin clears his front foot and digs this back towards Nathan Lyon.
Nathan Lyon bowls this short and in line with the stumps. Ravichandran Ashwin goes on the back foot and blocks this towards the bowler.
A rare maiden over from Australia! This is bowled on a good length and outside off. Rohit Sharma is watchful as he blocks the ball into the off side.
Outside the off stump on a fuller length. Rohit Sharma dabs this towards point with soft hands.
Goes back to bowling full and outside the off pole. Rohit Sharma gets behind the line of the ball and defends this towards mid on.
Bowls this one on a good length and angles this in from just outside off. Rohit Sharma tucks this towards mid-wicket.
Delivers this on a fuller length as well and in line with the stumps. Rohit Sharma flicks this towards the mid-wicket fielder.
Pat Cummins bowls this on a fuller length and just outside the off pole. Rohit Sharma leans forward and blocks this solidly towards mid on.
Gets this one to spin down leg side on a shorter length. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to flick this fine but misses.
Loopy delivery bowled wider outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin strokes this throough covers and collects two runs.
Beaten! Gets the ball to skid through outside off on a fuller length. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes at this but does not connect.
Bowls this slightly short and at the stumps. Ravichandran Ashwin rocks back in the crease and tucks this towards mid-wicket.
Floats this one full and straight. Rohit Sharma shimmies down the wicket and clips this down to long on for one.
Nathan Lyon flights this full and on an off-stump line. Rohit Sharma dabs this to the right of the bowler.
Bowls this in line with the stumps on a good length. Ravichandran Ashwin eases this towards mid on.

Oh my! That ball has stayed really low. Pat Cummins serves this on a good length and outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to play at it but misses with the ball going way under his bat to the keeper.
Gets this one to nip back in from just outside the off stump in a good length. Ravichandran Ashwin misses his shot and gets hit on the pads.
This is on a good length and outside the off pole. Ravichandran Ashwin turns this towards the backward point fielder.

FOUR! More runs for India as Pat Cummins continues to concede runs! This is bowled full and angled in from outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin hits a controlled stroke towards deep backward point for four runs.
Pat Cummins bowls this slightly back of a length and outside the off stump. Rohit Sharma dabs this into the point region and takes a single.
Tosses this one full and outside the off pole. Ravichandran Ashwin gets a good stride forward and drives this to deep cover for a couple of runs.
Loopy delivery bowled full and straight. Ravichandran Ashwin blocks this back down the pitch towards  the bowler.
Huge appeal! This is full and spinning down leg from the middle stump. Ravichandran Ashwin misses his block and gets hit on the pads. The umpire remains unmoved.
Flights this one full and in line with the stumps. Ravichandran Ashwin pushes at this and gets an inside edge to short fine leg.
Bowls full and outside the off stump. Ravichandran Ashwin dabs this to the left of the bowler.

FOUR! Nathan Lyon gets the outside edge straight away! Floats this one full and allows the ball to keep its line outside off. Ravichandran Ashwin looks to push it away but gets an edge towards third man for four runs.
Full around off by Pat Cummins, Rohit Sharma pushes this one to cover.
Beaten! Good-length delivery in the channel outside off, Rohit Sharma stays inside the line and tries to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Another one on a good length outside off, Rohit Sharma taps it towards point and wants a single. But eventually sends Ravichandran Ashwin back just in time.
On a good length angling in on off, Rohit Sharma blocks this one out on the off side.
Shorter in length, outside off, Rohit Sharma hangs back and works it to mid-wicket.
Starts with a full delivery outside off, Rohit Sharma pushes this one wide of deep point and collects a couple of runs.
Pat Cummins will share the attack and bowl from the other end.
Flighted delivery, full on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin gets behind the line and smothers the ball down the wicket.
Full and quicker on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin goes back and blocks this one out.
Flatter and quicker on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin defends this one from the crease to short leg.
Pushed straight, full and around off, Ravichandran Ashwin presses forward but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Rohit Sharma and India are underway on Day 2! Tossed up, full and on middle, Rohit Sharma steps out and pushes it down to long on for a single.
Murphy starts with a short delivery at the stumps, Rohit Sharma hangs back and defends it back to the bowler.

We are all set for the action to commence on Day 2. The umpires are out in the middle and the Australian players jog out onto the field to take their respective fielding positions. Rohit Sharma will look to build on his half-century and will take the field with the night watchman Ravichandran Ashwin. It will be spin to start off as Todd Murphy will begin proceedings. Let's go...

PITCH REPORT - Ajit Agarkar is joined by Matthew Hayden and he says that the wicket is shattered near the line of the stumps with the surface looking rough and it is like it has a layer of pebbles and gravel exposed near where the ball would pitch. Says that the only thing to expect from the wicket is spin, spin, and more spin. Ajit chips in by saying that there are a lot of runs to be made by the batters as well.

Australia were rocked early, losing both openers for low scores. Marnus Labuschagne, Steven Smith and Alex Carey got off to good starts, but nothing substantial to get the visitors to a challenging total. They also failed to trouble the Indian batters and have only one wicket to show for their efforts. The visitors will be hoping to get some early inroads in the first session. It promises to be yet another intriguing day of cricket. Will Australia fight their way back into the game? We shall find out soon, as the first ball of Day 2 is not too far away...

Despite losing the toss, India were off to a perfect start, with Mohammed Siraj and Mohammad Shami setting the tone for them. In the second session, Ravichandran Ashwin and Ravindra Jadeja ran through the visitors’ batting lineup. The hosts were equally good with the bat but lost KL Rahul an over before the close of play. With Rohit Sharma at the crease and plenty of batting still to come, India will be looking to build a healthy lead.

Hello and a warm welcome, ladies and gentlemen, to our coverage of Day 2 of the first Test between India and Australia at the Vidarbha Cricket Association Stadium in Nagpur. The opening day of the Test certainly lived up to expectations, and it was the hosts who took the ascendancy at the end. On the other hand, Australia did not have the best of days on the field and will need to start afresh on Day 2.
... DAY 2, SESSION 1 …

India are in control at the moment and will want to press their advantage further but it is just the end of Day 1. There is loads of action coming our way and Australia could easily find a way back into this game on Day 2. We will be back on Friday 10th February to see what transpires and the game will begin at 9.30 am IST (4 am GMT) but as you know do join us in advance for the build-up. Cheers!

Ravindra Jadeja is in for a quick chat. He says that he had nothing to do after 2 hours of rehab at NCA and hence he tried this hairstyle. Shares that he was enjoying bowling out there and is happy with the way he bowled. Adds that playing after 5 months is tough but he was working hard on fitness and skills at NCA which helped. Also says that playing the first-class game gave him confidence where he bowled 42 overs. Mentions that he was looking to target the stumps since the ball was not bouncing. Reckons that odd balls were spinning while some were keeping straight. Says that bowling for 10-12 hours every day at NCA helped him. Adds that he was working on his rhythm there. Ends by saying that is important not to think about the injury when making a comeback and that one should just go out thinking it as a normal series.

Australia will be disappointed with their start after winning the toss as India's two fast bowlers claimed the wickets of their openers inside the first three overs. Marnus Labuschagne and Steven Smith did a good job to steady the ship and took their side to Lunch without further damage. India came out in the second session with renewed vigor and took 6 wickets with Ravindra Jadeja leading the charge dismissing Marnus Labuschagne and Matt Renshaw on consecutive deliveries. Ashwin kicked off after getting his 450th test wicket and it was a session that well and truly belonged to India. Alex Carey and Peter Handscomb showed some fight with the former playing a good counter-attacking inning. With the way India have batted, the visitors will be disappointed that they did not apply themselves and build a few more partnerships.

SESSION SUMMARY - 80 runs, 27.5 overs, and 3 wickets. Another session goes India’s way as they have managed to bowl out their opponents and go into Day 2 with nine wickets in hand. They have brought the deficit down to 100 runs and will want to knock it off early before setting up a nice first-inning lead. Australia came out after Tea with two wickets left but managed to add just three runs to their total and were bowled out for 177 runs. Ravindra Jadeja took his fifth wicket and Ravichandran Ashwin added a third one to his kitty after which India were looking for a good start from their openers. Rohit Sharma came out all guns blazing scoring 13 runs in the first over and reached his half-century adding 76 for the first wicket with KL Rahul. The vice-captain departed just before stumps and will be disappointed after getting off to a start.
Full and on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin gets forward and defends it down the wicket. That will be STUMPS on Day 1!
Full and quicker on off, Ravichandran Ashwin takes a big stride forward and blocks this one out.
Lyon persists with full length and bowls it on middle, Ravichandran Ashwin smothers the ball on the off side.
Short and turning into the pads, Ravichandran Ashwin goes back in his crease and works it to short leg.
Fuller at the stumps, Rohit Sharma drives this one down to long on for a single.

A loud appeal but turned down! Nathan Lyon bowls this one full and quicker on off, Rohit Sharma leans forward to defend but gets rapped on the front pad. Australia go up in appeal but it is turned down by the umpire. They think of a review but decide against it.
Full and quicker at the stumps, Ravichandran Ashwin gets forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Ravichandran Ashwin walks out to bat at number 3 as a nightwatchman.

OUT! CAUGHT AND BOWLED! Todd Murphy gets his first wicket in Test cricket! Todd Murphy tosses this one full and around off, KL Rahul goes for the drive on the off side and plays it a bit early. The ball takes the inner part of the bat and lobs it back to the bowler. Todd Murphy makes no mistake and he is chuffed to bits. Australia will be relieved to break this partnership.
Flighted, full on off, KL Rahul gets forward and defends it on the off side.
Full and quicker outside off, KL Rahul defends it from the front foot.
Full and on off by Todd Murphy, KL Rahul leans forward and smothers the ball on the off side.
Short and at the pads, KL Rahul goes back in his crease and punches it wide of deep mid-wicket for a couple of runs.

FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries for Rohit Sharma! Nathan Lyon overpitches and bowls this one full and outside off, Rohit Sharma does not miss out and drives it firmly through the covers region for yet another boundary.

FOUR! FIFTY for Rohit Sharma! Nathan Lyon tosses this one full and on off, Rohit Sharma gets into the position early and paddles this one towards the fine leg region. Gets it to the right of short fine leg and collects a boundary to bring up his fifty.

Lyon switches to over the wicket and bowls it short and turning into the batter, KL Rahul hangs back and punches it to mid-wicket.
Full and on off, KL Rahul works this one from the front foot to mid-wicket.
Flighted, full around off, Rohit Sharma drives this one through the vacant covers region. Pat Cummins performs the chase and saves a run for his side.
Full and flatter on middle, KL Rahul leans forward and defends it down the wicket.
Floated, full at the pads, Rohit Sharma uses his feet and clips it to deep mid-wicket for a single.
Full and on middle by Todd Murphy, Rohit Sharma advances and pushes it back to the bowler.
Flighted, full on middle, KL Rahul uses his feet and knocks it down to long on for a single.
Full and at the stumps, KL Rahul defends this one form the front foot.
Tossed up, full and on middle, KL Rahul gets forward and defends it to short leg.
Full and quicker on off, Rohit Sharma stays in the crease and tries to defend but gets beaten on the outside edge.
Floated, full around off, Rohit Sharma takes a stride forward and defends it down the wicket.
Short and down the leg side, Rohit Sharma shapes to pull but the ball keeps very low and he fails to connect. Alex Carey behind the wicket dives to his left and collects it cleanly.

Right then. That's it from the coverage of this match. India have taken an early lead in this series and have left the Aussies with a lot of thinking to do. There are three more Test matches left in this series. So, there is still a long way to go. These two sides now will head to Delhi as the second Test match will be contested in the Arun Jaitley Stadium. The first ball will be at 9.30 am IST (4 am GMT). But as you all know you can join us early for the build-up. Until then, take care and goodbye!

Ravindra Jadeja is the Player of the Match for for his all-round brilliance scoring 70 runs and taking 7 wickets in the match. Feels amazing making a come back after 5 months. Shares that he was working hard on his skills at NCA while doing rehab. Thanks the staff at NCA for working hard with him during that period. Adds that he looked to bowl in good areas and tried to keep it within the stumps considering that Australian like to sweep. Mentions that he keeps things simple with the bat and tries not to change anything. Ends by saying that he is focusing more on his batting since it is a crucial positon in the batting order.

Rohit Sharma, the victorious skipper is in for a chat. He says that surely the century was a special one. Mentions it was important for them to start well and he is happy that he could put up a performance that helped his side. Adds that he was unfortunate to miss a few Test matches dew to injuries. Informs, since being appointed as the Test captain he has only played twice, but he has been ready for this Test match, and he is quite aware of how to come back from the injuries. Mentions you need some sort of applications, mind set and a concentrete plan on these Indian pitches. Adds he has grown up playing on surfaces that spin a lot, so that means they need to be unorthodox, use a lot of feet. Also adds that a batter needs to understand what are their strengths and works their way accordingly. Adds that the seamers set the tone well. Shami and Siraj certainly know how to work on such wickets. Praises all the batters for their effort but nevertheless, the spinners as well.

Pat Cummins, the skipper of Australia, says that the game moves quickly at times in India. Adds that India played really well and it is tough with their spinners bowling. Mentions that Rohit showed his class with the bat. Feels that the wicket was spinning in the first innings but it wasn't unplayable. Also says that they would have loved to get 100 runs more. Adds that starting here is tough and 3-4 guys got starts but could not carry on. Ends by saying that Murphy was fantastic on debut and he has been impressive ever since coming on the radar.
Stay tuned for the presentation...

Ravichandran Ashwin is in for a flash interview. He credits the batting unit as they dug deep and kept Australia on the field for long periods. Shares that the since the wicket was slow and had low bounce, his plan was to lure the batters into the drive. Mentions that Ravindra Jadeja has been in phenomenal form for the past 3 years with the way he has batted and bowled. Adds that he is thankful for having a bowling partner like him. Feels that Axar Patel is no ordinary bowler either and they have a good set of spinners as all can bat as well. Feels that Australia is a world-class side and they will introspect and come back stronger in the next Test. Ends by saying that he looks forward to more opportunities to bat as a night watchman.

Rohit Sharma certainly played a captain's knock in reply. He recorded his first ever century against Australia and it couldn't have come at a better time. Although, India were put under the spotlight when no other batter in the top-order sticked around for long. India were 168 for 5 at one stage and it looked like the Aussies had them by the scruff of the neck. That's when Ravindra Jadeja showed his class and graced the Nagpur crowd with his sword celebration after getting his half-century. He was supported well by Axar Patel who fell agonizingly short of his century by just 16 runs as India got all-out for 400. Mohammad Shami also hit a few lusty blows as his contribution. It was Todd Murphy who stood out with the ball for Australia with his seven-wicket haul. Australia then came out to bat with a defecit of 223 runs but it proved to be way too much for them.

So, winning the toss remains the only highlight for Australia in this Test match. After opting to bat first, Australian batter could not justify their skipper's decision as they were bundled out for just 177 runs. David Warner and Usman Khawaja were sent back for just one run. Marnus Labuschagne and Steven Smith stitched a solid stand to get their innings back on track, but once this stand was broken no other batter, except Alex Carey and Peter Handscomb looked comfortable at the crease. Also, the Aussies need to focus on their contribution from the lower end as well with the blade. For India, Ravindra Jadeja marked a strong comeback with a fi-fer. Ravichandran Ashwin chipped in with three wickets as well.

India once again were the dominant side with the ball. As it was seen in the morning session, the pitch just had too much venom in it. The spin twin attack of Ravichandran Ashwin and Ravindra Jadeja that dismantled the top-order. Ravichandran Ashwin picked up yet another fi-fer in his Test career. He continues on his merry way in red-ball cricket. Ravindra Jadeja never looked like he was away from the game as he took a couple here, while Axar Patel chipped in with a wicket as well. Mohammad Shami came in at the end and completed the job with two wickets to his name.

Australia were lacklustre once again with the bat in this Test match and have an unwanted record on their side now, as this is their second-lowest score against India. Australia have been bowled out in almost a little over session here. They certainly need to head back to their drawing board and come out with some new strategies ahead of the second Test in Delhi. Their opening pair could not set the platform and that opened the gate for India. Only Steven Smith was the lone batter who could survive till the very end but could not do much harm.

WOW! India dominated the first Test match and they have gone one step ahead in their dream of battling it out once again in the finals of the World Test Championship. The hosts take a 1-nil lead in this series with a comprehensive win by an innings and 132 runs. Australia though are left with a lot to ponder on.

OUT! LBW! IT'S ALL OVER! Mohammad Shami bowls this it on a good length and angling into the batter, Scott Boland gets beaten for pace and fails to get his bat down in time. The ball catches him on the back leg and the umpire raises his finger. He has a word with Steven Smith and sends it upstairs. The UltraEdge shows no bat and on BallTracking it is umpire's call on hitting. The on-field decision stands and it brings an end to Australia's troubles with the bat. India win by an innings and 132 runs and take a 1-0 lead in the series.
